    fields: [proc.name, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, contains]
    values:
    - [[java], sdjagent.jar]
    - [[oneagentos], oneagentos]
    - [[sh], '"then exec curl http://localhost:9090"']
    - [[sh, wget], "http://localhost:9090/-/"]
    - [[sh], "https://localhost:2379/health"]
    - [[sh], "https://localhost:12386/v0/ping"]
    - [[sh], "https://localhost:12385/enzi/_ping"]
    - [[sh], "https://localhost:2375/_ping"]
  - name: proc_cmdline_startswith
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
    values:
    - ["grpc_health_pro"]
    - ["gunicorn"]
    - ["fping6"]
    - ["vasd /opt"]
    - ["fping"]
    - ["ceph"]
    - ["erl_child_setup"]
    - ["conmon"]
  - name: parent_proc_name
    fields: [proc.pname, proc.name]
    comps: ["=", "="]
    values:
    - [bluematador-col, df]
    - [runc, sh]
    - [argoexec, uname]
    - [erl_child_setup, sh]
    - [runc, pgrep]
    - [sh, df]
    - [cat, ngnix]
    - [haproxy, "check_mke_api.s"]
    - [timeout, "check_mke_api.s"]
    - [haproxy, "check_k8s_api.s"]
    - [keepalived, "check_mke_api.s"]
    - ["check_mke_api.s", timeout]
    - ["check_mke_api.s", grep]
    - ["check_k8s_api.s", timeout]
    - ["cldb_monitor", "maprexecute"]
    - ["alerta", "uname"]
    - ["sh", "irisstart"]
  - name: proc_new_uid
    fields: [proc.name, evt.arg.uid]
    values:
    - [nrpe, nagios]
  - name: user_new_uid
    fields: [user.name, evt.arg.uid]
    values:
    - [nobody, nobody]
    - [www-data, www-data]
    - [_apt, _apt]
    - [postfix, postfix]
    - [pki-agent, pki-agent]
    - [pki-acme, pki-acme]
    - [nfsnobody, nfsnobody]
    - [postgres, postgres]
  - name: user_uid_new_uid
    fields: [user.uid, evt.arg.uid]
  - name: proc_name_image_startswith
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, startswith]
  - name: proc_pname_image_startswith
    fields: [proc.pname, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, startswith]
    values:
    - [[nginx], "k8s.gcr.io/ingress-nginx/controller-chroot"]
    - [[nginx], "registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller-chroot"]
    - [[ngnix], "us.gcr.io/k8s-artifacts-prod/ingress-nginx/controller"]
    - [["blackduck-uploa"], "blackducksoftware/blackduck-upload-cache"]
  - name: proc_pname_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.pname, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [["healthcheck.sh"], "validsign/oss-single-sign-on"]
    - [["start.sh"], "/acryldata/datahub-gms"]
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [[sleep], "ghcr.io/adelerhof/toolbox"]
    - [[sleep], "mirantis/ucp-metrics"]
  - name: proc_cmdline_container_image_repo
    fields: [proc.cmdline, container.image.repository]
    comps: [startswith, startswith]
    values:
    - ["pgrep -f .*register-the-runner", "registry.gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab-runner"]
    - ["pgrep gitlab.*runner", "registry.gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab-runner"]
  - name: proc_cmdline_endswith_container_image_repo
    fields: [proc.cmdline, container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith, startswith]
    values:
    - ["-c while true; do sleep 1; done", "docker.io/ngrok/ngrok"]
  - name: proc_cmdline_contains_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.cmdline, container.image.repository]
    comps: [contains, endswith]
  - name: pcmdline_contains_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.pcmdline, container.image.repository]
    comps: [contains, endswith]
    values:
    - ["http://127.0.0.1:8500/v1/status/leader", "docker.io/hashicorp/consul"]
  - name: proc_anames_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.aname, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [["blackduck-uploa"], "blackducksoftware/blackduck-upload-cache"]
    - [["rabbitmq-server", "erl_child_setup"], "blackducksoftware/rabbitmq"]
  - name: image_suffix
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith]
    values:
    - ["docker.io/hashicorp/consul"]
    - ["/cerberus/vault"]
    - ["/prometheus"]
    - ["/sonarqube-dxo-k8s"]
  - name: proc_pname_aname
    fields: [proc.pname, proc.aname]
    comps: [in, in]
    values:
    - [["php-fpm7"], ["supervisord"]]
    - [[argoexec], [argoexec]]
    - [[logrotate], ["gitlab-logrotat"]]
  output: >
    Unexpected setuid call by non-sudo, non-root program (user.name=%user.name user_loginuid=%user.loginuid user.uid=%user.uid proc.name=%proc.name parent=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4]
    proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline uid=%evt.arg.uid container.id=%container.id evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [users, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.1, NIST, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-6(9), NIST_800-53_AC-6(10), NIST_800-53_AU-6(8), ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.2.3, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(a), HIPAA_164.312(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, GDPR, GDPR_32.1, GDPR_32.2, MITRE, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_T1548.001_abuse_elevation_control_mechanism_setuid_and_setgid MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation]

- macro: user_known_user_management_activities
  condition: (never_true)

- macro: chage_list
  condition: (proc.name=chage and (proc.cmdline contains "-l" or proc.cmdline contains "--list"))

- macro: chsh_agent
  condition: (proc.cmdline startswith "chsh" and proc.pname startswith "agent")

- macro: gpasswd_agent
  condition: (proc.cmdline startswith "gpasswd" and proc.pname startswith "agent")

- rule: User mgmt binaries
  desc: >
    activity by any programs that can manage users, passwords, or permissions. sudo and su are excluded.
    Activity in containers is also excluded--some containers create custom users on top
    of a base linux distribution at startup.
    Some innocuous commandlines that don't actually change anything are excluded.
  condition: >
    spawned_process and proc.name in (user_mgmt_binaries) and
    not container and
    not run_by_qualys and
    not run_by_sumologic_securefiles and
    not run_by_yum and
    not run_by_ms_oms and
    not run_by_google_accounts_daemon and
    not chage_list and
    not user_known_user_management_activities and
    not chsh_agent and
    not gpasswd_agent
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_names
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
    values: [su, sudo, lastlog, nologin, unix_chkpwd]
  - name: proc_pnames
    fields: proc.pname
    comps: in
    values: [cron_binaries, systemd, systemd.postins, udev.postinst, run-parts, refresh-mcollec, "chef-client", "ssm-session-wor"]
  - name: cmdline_prefixes
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
    values:
    - ["passwd -S"]
    - ["useradd -D"]
    - ["systemd --version"]
    - ["groupadd google-sudoers"]
    - ["usermod -aG google-sudoers"]
  - name: proc_cmdline_pname
    fields: [proc.cmdline, proc.pname]
    comps: [endswith, "="]
    values:
    - ["usermod --help", "python"]
  output: >
    User management binary command run outside of container
    (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline parent=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name gggparent=%proc.aname[4])
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [host, users, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.1, SOC2_CC6.6, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.1.1, NIST_800-171_3.1.2, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-2, NIST_800-53_AC-2(4), NIST_800-53_AC-3, NIST_800-53_AC-6(9), NIST_800-53_AC-6(10), FedRAMP, FedRAMP_AC-2, FedRAMP_AC-2(4), ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.2.3, ISO_27001_A.9.4.4, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.310(a), HIPAA_164.310(b), HIPAA_164.312(a), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, GDPR, GDPR_32.1, GDPR_32.2, MITRE, MITRE_T1068_explotation_for_privilege_escalation, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation]

- list: allowed_dev_files
  items: [/dev/null, /dev/stdin, /dev/stdout, /dev/stderr, /dev/random, /dev/urandom, /dev/console, /dev/kmsg, /dev/termination-log]

- macro: user_known_create_files_below_dev_activities
  condition: (never_true)

- rule: Scripting Language Execution below dev
  desc: This rule detects scripting language execution from below the /dev directory
  condition: spawned_process and ((proc.cwd startswith "/dev") or (proc.args contains "/dev/" and not (proc.cmdline contains "> /dev/null" or proc.cmdline contains ">/dev/null"))) and ((proc.exepath startswith "/dev") or (interpreted_procs) or (shell_procs and not (proc.cmdline contains "-c" or proc.pcmdline contains "-c")))
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_cmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: proc_pcmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.pcmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: container_image_contains
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [in]
  - name: container_proc_cmdline
    fields: [container.image.repository, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, contains]
  - name: proc_name_cmdline_startswith
    fields: [proc.name, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, startswith]
  output: "Scripting language execution detected below /dev (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline connection=%fd.name user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid container.id=%container.id evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath proc.name=%proc.name user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)"
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [MITRE, MITRE_TA0002_execution, MITRE_T1059_command_and_scripting_interpreter]

# (we may need to add additional checks against false positives, see:
# https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/rkhunter/+bug/86153)
- rule: Create files below dev
  desc: creating any files below /dev other than known programs that manage devices. Some rootkits hide files in /dev.
  condition: >
    fd.directory = /dev and
    (evt.type = creat or ((evt.type = open or evt.type = openat) and evt.arg.flags contains O_CREAT))
    and not fd.name startswith /dev/tty
    and not user_known_create_files_below_dev_activities
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_names
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
    values: [dev_creation_binaries]
  - name: file_names
    fields: fd.name
    comps: in
    values: [allowed_dev_files]
  - name: proc_file
    fields: [proc.name, fd.name]
  - name: proc_file_prefix
    fields: [proc.name, fd.name]
    comps: [in, startswith]
  output: "File created below /dev by untrusted program (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline file=%fd.name container.id=%container.id evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)"
  priority: ERROR
  tags: [filesystem, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.8, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.14.7, NIST_800-171_3.3.1, NIST_800-171_3.3.2, NIST_800-190, NIST_800-190_3.4.4, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-6(9), NIST_800-53_AC-6(10), NIST_800-53_AU-6(8), NIST_800-53_SI-4, NIST_800-53_AU-2, FedRAMP, FedRAMP_AU-2, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.2.3, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(a), HIPAA_164.312(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_01.p, HITRUST_CSF_01.s, HITRUST_CSF_01.x, HITRUST_CSF_06.i, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ac, HITRUST_CSF_09.ad, HITRUST_CSF_09.ae, HITRUST_CSF_09.m, HITRUST_CSF_11.a, HITRUST_CSF_11.b, GDPR, GDPR_32.1, GDPR_32.2, MITRE, MITRE_T1036_masquerading, MITRE_T1036.005_masquerading_match_legitimate_name_or_location, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_T1027_obfuscated_files_or_information]


# In a local/user rules file, you could override this macro to
# explicitly enumerate the container images that you want to allow
# access to EC2 metadata. In this main falco rules file, there isn't
# any way to know all the containers that should have access, so any
# container is alllowed, by repeating the "container" macro. In the
# overridden macro, the condition would look something like
# (container.image.repository = vendor/container-1 or
# container.image.repository = vendor/container-2 or ...)
- macro: ec2_metadata_containers
  condition: container

# On EC2 instances, 169.254.169.254 is a special IP used to fetch
# metadata about the instance. It may be desirable to prevent access
# to this IP from containers.
- rule: Contact EC2 Instance Metadata Service From Container
  desc: Detect attempts to contact the EC2 Instance Metadata Service from a container
  condition: outbound and fd.sip="169.254.169.254" and container and (proc.args contains "/meta-data/iam/info" or proc.args contains "/ec2/security-credentials/" or proc.args contains "/iam/security-credentials")
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [[dragent], "docker.io/sysdig/agent"]
    - [["aws-k8s-agent"], "amazonaws.com/amazon-k8s-cni"]
  - name: container_image_in
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [sysdig_commercial_images, gke_trusted_images_launch_root_list, "docker.io/sysdiglabs/k8sauditlogforwarder"]
  - name: proc_name_cmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.name, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, contains]
  - name: proc_pname_pcmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.pname, proc.pcmdline]
    comps: [in, contains]
  - name: proc_pcmdline_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.pcmdline, container.image.repository]
    comps: [startswith, endswith]
    values:
    - ["bash /opt/streamsets-datacollector-3.16.0/", "amazonaws.com/feeds/bikes/streamsets"]
  output: Outbound connection to EC2 instance metadata service (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.name=%proc.name proc.args=%proc.args proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] connection=%fd.name %container.info evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag)
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [network, aws, container, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.8, SOC2_CC6.1, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.1.1, NIST_800-171_3.1.2, NIST_800-171_3.1.3, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.14.7, NIST_800-171_3.4.6, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-4, NIST_800-53_AC-17, NIST_800-53_SI-4(18), NIST_800-53_SI-4, NIST_800-53_CM-7, FedRAMP, FedRAMP_CM-7, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.1.2, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.310(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_01.i, HITRUST_CSF_01.j, HITRUST_CSF_01.l, HITRUST_CSF_01.n, HITRUST_CSF_01.x, HITRUST_CSF_01.y, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ac, HITRUST_CSF_09.i, HITRUST_CSF_09.m, HITRUST_CSF_09.s, HITRUST_CSF_10.j, HITRUST_CSF_10.m, HITRUST_CSF_11.a, HITRUST_CSF_11.b, GDPR, GDPR_32.1, GDPR_32.2, MITRE, MITRE_T1552_unsecured_credentials, MITRE_T1552.005_unsecured_credentials_cloud_instance_metadata_api, MITRE_TA0006_credential_access, MITRE_TA0007_discovery]

# This rule is not enabled by default, since this rule is for cloud environment(GCP, AWS and Azure) only.
# If you want to enable this rule, overwrite the first macro,
# And you can filter the container that you want to allow access to metadata by overwriting the second macro.
- macro: consider_metadata_access
  condition: (never_true)

- macro: user_known_metadata_access
  condition: (never_true)

# On GCP, AWS and Azure, 169.254.169.254 is a special IP used to fetch
# metadata about the instance. The metadata could be used to get credentials by attackers.
- rule: Contact cloud metadata service from container
  desc: Detect attempts to contact the Cloud Instance Metadata Service from a container
  condition: outbound and fd.sip="169.254.169.254" and container and consider_metadata_access and not user_known_metadata_access
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [[flb-pipeline, fluent-bit], fluent/fluent-bit]
    - [["external-secret"], "ghcr.io/external-secrets/external-secrets"]
  - name: proc_name
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
    values: ["gke-mcs-importe", prometheus, "gke-metadata-se"]
  - name: container_image_in
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [sysdig_commercial_images, "gcr.io/stackdriver-agents/stackdriver-logging-agent"]
  output: Outbound connection to cloud instance metadata service (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline connection=%fd.name %container.info evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag)
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [network, container, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.8, SOC2_CC6.1, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.1.1, NIST_800-171_3.1.2, NIST_800-171_3.1.3, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.14.7, NIST_800-171_3.4.6, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-4, NIST_800-53_AC-17, NIST_800-53_SI-4(18), NIST_800-53_SI-4, NIST_800-53_CM-7, FedRAMP, FedRAMP_CM-7, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.1.2, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.310(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_01.i, HITRUST_CSF_01.j, HITRUST_CSF_01.l, HITRUST_CSF_01.n, HITRUST_CSF_01.x, HITRUST_CSF_01.y, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ac, HITRUST_CSF_09.i, HITRUST_CSF_09.m, HITRUST_CSF_09.s, HITRUST_CSF_10.j, HITRUST_CSF_10.m, HITRUST_CSF_11.a, HITRUST_CSF_11.b, GDPR, GDPR_32.1, GDPR_32.2, MITRE, MITRE_T1552_unsecured_credentials, MITRE_TA0006_credential_access, MITRE_TA0007_discovery, MITRE_T1552.005_unsecured_credentials_cloud_instance_metadata_api]


- macro: private_aws_credentials
  condition: >
    (proc.args icontains "aws_access_key_id" or
    proc.args icontains "aws_secret_access_key" or
    proc.args icontains "aws_session_token" or
    proc.args icontains "accesskeyid" or
    proc.args icontains "secretaccesskey")

- macro: whitelist_acme_sh
  condition: ((proc.pname="acme.sh" or proc.aname[2]="acme.sh") and (proc.cmdline startswith "grep -n" and proc.cmdline endswith "= /root/.acme.sh/account.conf"))

- rule: Find AWS Credentials
  desc: Find or grep AWS credentials
  condition: >
    spawned_process and
    ((grep_commands and private_aws_credentials) or
    (proc.name = "find" and proc.args endswith ".aws/credentials"))
    and not whitelist_acme_sh
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_pname
    fields: [proc.name, proc.pname]
  - name: proc_cmdline
    fields: [proc.name, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, startswith]
  - name: proc_pcmdline
    fields: [proc.pcmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
  - name: container_image_repository
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [sysdig_commercial_images, "quay.io/argoproj/argoexec", "docker.io/hashicorp/vault", "docker.atl-paas.net/sox/buildeng/agent-baseagent", "quay.io/prometheus/node-exporter", "quay.io/prometheus/prometheus"]
  - name: proc_aname_2
    fields: proc.aname[2]
    comps: in
    values: [qualys_binaries, "ovalprobes"]
  - name: container_name_startswith
    fields: [container.name]
    comps: [startswith]
    values:
    - ["qcsimagescanning"]
  output: Search AWS credentials activities found (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline container.id=%container.id container_name=%container.name evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag evt.args=%evt.args)
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [MITRE_TA0006_credential_access, MITRE_TA0007_discovery, MITRE_T1552_unsecured_credentials, process, aws]


# In a local/user rules file, list the namespace or container images that are
# allowed to contact the K8s API Server from within a container. This
# might cover cases where the K8s infrastructure itself is running
# within a container.
- macro: k8s_containers
  condition: >
    (container.image.repository in (gcr.io/google_containers/hyperkube-amd64,
     gcr.io/google_containers/kube2sky, docker.io/sysdig/falco,
     docker.io/sysdig/sysdig, docker.io/falcosecurity/falco,
     sysdig/falco, sysdig/sysdig, falcosecurity/falco, fluent/fluentd-kubernetes-daemonset, prom/prometheus, ibm_cloud_containers,
     public.ecr.aws/falcosecurity/falco, quay.io/sysdig/agent, quay.io/openshift-release-dev/ocp-v4.0-art-dev)
     or (k8s.ns.name = "kube-system"))

- list: known_k8s_api_programs
  items: [prometheus, airflow]

- macro: k8s_api_server
  condition: (fd.sip.name="1.2.3.4")

- macro: user_known_contact_k8s_api_server_activities
  condition: (never_true)

- rule: Contact K8S API Server From Container
  desc: Detect attempts to contact the K8S API Server from a container
  condition: >
    evt.type=connect and evt.dir=< and
    (fd.typechar=4 or fd.typechar=6) and
    container and
    not k8s_containers and
    k8s_api_server and
    not user_known_contact_k8s_api_server_activities
    and not calico_node
    and not proc.name in (known_k8s_api_programs)
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [[flb-pipeline, fluent-bit], fluent/fluent-bit]
  - name: proc_name_cmdline_startswith
    fields: [proc.name, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, startswith]
    values:
    - [[coredns], "coredns -conf"]
  - name: container_image_repo_in
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [sysdig_commercial_images]
  output: Unexpected connection to K8s API Server from container (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline %container.info image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name connection=%fd.name)
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [network, k8s, container, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.1, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.1.1, NIST_800-171_3.1.2, NIST_800-171_3.1.3, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.14.7, NIST_800-190, NIST_800-190_3.4.2, NIST_800-190_3.4.4, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-4, NIST_800-53_AC-17, NIST_800-53_SI-4(18), NIST_800-53_SI-4, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.1.2, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.310(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.i, HITRUST_CSF_01.j, HITRUST_CSF_01.n, HITRUST_CSF_01.x, HITRUST_CSF_01.y, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ac, HITRUST_CSF_09.m, HITRUST_CSF_09.s, HITRUST_CSF_11.a, HITRUST_CSF_11.b, GDPR, GDPR_32.1, GDPR_32.2, MITRE, MITRE_T1552.007_unsecured_credentials_container_api, MITRE_TA0007_discovery, MITRE_T1609_continer_administration_command, MITRE_TA0002_execution]

# In a local/user rules file, list the container images that are
# allowed to contact NodePort services from within a container. This
# might cover cases where the K8s infrastructure itself is running
# within a container.
#
# By default, all containers are allowed to contact NodePort services.
- macro: nodeport_containers
  condition: container

- rule: Unexpected K8s NodePort Connection
  desc: Detect attempts to use K8s NodePorts from a container
  condition: (inbound_outbound) and fd.sport >= 30000 and fd.sport <= 32767 and container and not nodeport_containers
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  output: Unexpected K8s NodePort Connection (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline connection=%fd.name container.id=%container.id evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [network, k8s, container, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.1, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.1.1, NIST_800-171_3.1.2, NIST_800-171_3.1.3, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.14.7, NIST_800-190, NIST_800-190_3.4.1, NIST_800-190_3.4.2, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-4, NIST_800-53_AC-17, NIST_800-53_SI-4(18), NIST_800-53_SI-4, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.1.2, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.310(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.i, HITRUST_CSF_01.j, HITRUST_CSF_01.n, HITRUST_CSF_01.x, HITRUST_CSF_01.y, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ac, HITRUST_CSF_09.m, HITRUST_CSF_09.s, HITRUST_CSF_11.a, HITRUST_CSF_11.b, GDPR, GDPR_32.1, GDPR_32.2, MITRE, MITRE_T1205.001_port_knocking]

- list: network_tool_binaries
  items: [nc, ncat, netcat, nmap, tcpdump, tshark, ngrep, telnet, mitmproxy, socat, zmap, graftcp, mgraftcp, "graftcp-local", smbclient]

- macro: network_tool_procs
  condition: (proc.name in (network_tool_binaries))

# In a local/user rules file, create a condition that matches legitimate uses
# of a package management process inside a container.
#
# For example:
# - macro: user_known_package_manager_in_container
#   condition: proc.cmdline="dpkg -l"
- macro: user_known_package_manager_in_container
  condition: (never_true)

- macro: package_listing
  condition: (proc.cmdline startswith "apt list" or  proc.cmdline startswith "pip3 list" or proc.cmdline startswith "dpkg -l" or proc.cmdline startswith "apk info" or proc.cmdline startswith "rpm -qa" or proc.cmdline startswith "dpkg --print-architecture" or proc.cmdline="apk -V" or proc.cmdline startswith "apk manifest" or proc.cmdline startswith "dpkg --list" or proc.cmdline endswith "gem --version" or proc.cmdline startswith "update-alternat --list" or proc.cmdline startswith "rpm -q --changelog" or proc.cmdline startswith "rpm -E" or proc.cmdline startswith "dpkg --compare-versions" or proc.cmdline startswith "microdnf clean" or proc.cmdline startswith "rpm --query --all" or proc.cmdline startswith "rpm -q" or proc.cmdline startswith "apt-get check" or proc.cmdline contains "-m pip show" or proc.cmdline contains "-m pip list" or proc.pcmdline startswith "sh -c dpkg 2> /dev/null -S" or proc.cmdline startswith "pip3 /usr/local/bin/pip3 list" or proc.cmdline startswith "pip /usr/local/bin/pip list")

- macro: package_changes
  condition: (proc.cmdline contains "install" or proc.cmdline contains "update" or proc.cmdline contains "delete" or proc.cmdline contains "upgrade" or proc.cmdline contains "remove" or proc.cmdline contains " add " or proc.cmdline contains " del " or proc.cmdline contains "cache")

# Container is supposed to be immutable. Package management should be done in building the image.
- rule: Launch Package Management Process in Container
  desc: Package management process ran inside container
  condition: >
    spawned_process
    and container
    and user.name != "_apt"
    and package_mgmt_procs
    and package_changes
    and not package_mgmt_ancestor_procs
    and not package_listing
    and not user_known_package_manager_in_container
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [[rpm], "/sysdig/node-image-analyzer"]
    - [["apt-get", "apt-config", dpkg], "mcr.microsoft.com/azuremonitor/containerinsights/ciprod"]
  - name: proc_pname_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.pname, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [["openshift-docke", "openshift-sti-b"], "quay.io/openshift-release-dev/ocp-v4.0-art-dev"]
  - name: proc_name_image_prefix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, startswith]
  - name: container_name_image_prefix
    fields: [container.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [contains, startswith]
  - name: container_image_in
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [sysdig_commercial_images]
  - name: container_image_suffix
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith]
    values:
    - ["/sysdig/kspm-analyzer"]
    - ["/kubernetes/kube-proxy"]
  - name: proc_name_aname
    fields: [proc.name, proc.aname]
    comps: [in, in]
    values:
    - [["rpm"], ["anchore-manager", "cortex-xdr-payl"]]
    - [["update-alternat"], ["cilium-agent"]]
    - [["alternatives"], ["run-jnlp-client"]]
    - [[exe], [chromedriver]]
  output: >
    Package management process launched in container (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline container.id=%container.id container_name=%container.name evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag)
  priority: ERROR
  tags: [process, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.1, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.14.1, NIST_800-171_3.14.2, NIST_800-171_3.14.3, NIST_800-171_3.14.4, NIST_800-171_3.14.5, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.14.7, NIST_800-171_3.4.5, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_CM-5, NIST_800-53_SI-7, NIST_800-53_SI-4, NIST_800-53_SI-3, FedRAMP, FedRAMP_SI-3, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.12.5.1, ISO_27001_A.12.6.2, ISO_27001_A.14.2.4, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(c), HIPAA_164.312(e), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.x, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ac, HITRUST_CSF_09.b, HITRUST_CSF_09.j, HITRUST_CSF_09.k, HITRUST_CSF_09.m, HITRUST_CSF_10.c, HITRUST_CSF_10.j, HITRUST_CSF_10.k, HITRUST_CSF_11.a, HITRUST_CSF_11.b, GDPR, GDPR_32.1, GDPR_32.2, MITRE, MITRE_T1068_explotation_for_privilege_escalation, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation]

- rule: Netcat Remote Code Execution in Container
  desc: Netcat Program runs inside container that allows remote code execution
  condition: >
    spawned_process and container and
    ((proc.name = "nc" and (proc.cmdline contains " -e " or proc.cmdline contains " -c ")) or
     (proc.name = "ncat" and (proc.cmdline contains " --sh-exec " or proc.cmdline contains " --exec " or proc.cmdline contains " -e "
                              or proc.cmdline contains " -c " or proc.cmdline contains " --lua-exec "))
    )
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [[nc], "rancher/rke-tools"]
  - name: proc_name_cmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.name, proc.cmdline]
    comps: ["=", contains]
  - name: container_name_image_prefix
    fields: [container.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [contains, startswith]
  - name: container_name_image_prefix_cmdline_contains
    fields: [container.name, container.image.repository, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [contains, startswith, contains]
  - name: cmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [contains]
    values:
    - ["echo -e"]
    - ["-cbk-"]
    - ["ml-graphql-engine"]
    - ["us-east"]
    - ["-clickhouse"]
    - ["-eu."]
    - ["-covid"]
  output: >
    Netcat runs inside container that allows remote code execution (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline container.id=%container.id container_name=%container.name evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [network, process, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.1, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.14.1, NIST_800-171_3.14.2, NIST_800-171_3.14.3, NIST_800-171_3.14.4, NIST_800-171_3.14.5, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.14.7, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-6(9), NIST_800-53_AC-6(10), NIST_800-53_AU-6(8), NIST_800-53_SI-3, NIST_800-53_SI-4, FedRAMP, FedRAMP_SI-3, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.4.4, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(a), HIPAA_164.312(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_01.x, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ac, HITRUST_CSF_09.j, HITRUST_CSF_09.k, HITRUST_CSF_09.m, HITRUST_CSF_11.a, HITRUST_CSF_11.b, GDPR, GDPR_32.1, GDPR_32.2, MITRE, MITRE_TA0002_execution, MITRE_TA0007_discovery, MITRE_T1049_system_network_connections_discovery]

- macro: user_known_network_tool_activities
  condition: (never_true)

- macro: netcat_localhost
  condition: (proc.name=nc and (proc.cmdline startswith "nc 127.0.0.1" or proc.cmdline startswith "nc localhost" or proc.cmdline startswith "nc -z 127.0.0.1" or proc.cmdline startswith "nc -w2 localhost" or proc.cmdline startswith "nc -w 2 localhost" or proc.cmdline startswith "nc -vz 127.0.0.1" or proc.cmdline startswith "nc -z localhost" or proc.cmdline startswith "nc -z localhost" or proc.cmdline startswith "nc -vz -w 1 localhost"))

- macro: openssl_connection
  condition: (proc.name=openssl and proc.cmdline contains "s_client" and proc.cmdline contains "-connect")

- list: malicious_download_tools
  items: [ab, aria2c, lwp-download]

- macro: proc_in_malicious_download_tools
  condition: proc.name in (malicious_download_tools)

- rule: Launch Suspicious Network Tool in Container
  desc: Detect network tools launched inside container
  condition: >
    spawned_process and container and (network_tool_procs or openssl_connection or proc_in_malicious_download_tools) and not user_known_network_tool_activities and not netcat_localhost
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [[nc], "sysdig/cassandra"]
    - [[nc], "sysdig/cassandra-3"]
    - [[nc], "bitnami/zookeeper"]
    - [[nc], "/zookeeper"]
    - [[nc], "/kafka"]
    - [[dig], "openshift-release-dev/ocp-v4.0-art-dev"]
    - [[dig], "obs/ibm-storage-metrics-agent"]
    - [[nc], "cia/kube-logging"]
  - name: proc_name_image
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, in]
    values:
    - [[nc], ["zookeeper"]]
  - name: proc_name_proc_pname_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, proc.pname, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, in, endswith]
    values:
    - [[nc], [wait_for_rabbit], "openzaak/open-notificaties"]
  - name: proc_name_cmdline_startswith
    fields: [proc.name, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, startswith]
    values:
    - [[dig], "dig @127.0.0.1"]
    - [[dig], "dig -t A @172.21.0.10"]
  - name: proc_anames_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.aname, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [["LightJobConsume"], "apm/synthetics-minion"]
  output: >
    Network tool launched in container (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline parent_process=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] container.id=%container.id container_name=%container.name evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag)
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [network, process, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.1, SOC2_CC6.7, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.14.1, NIST_800-171_3.14.2, NIST_800-171_3.14.3, NIST_800-171_3.14.4, NIST_800-171_3.14.5, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.14.7, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-6(9), NIST_800-53_AC-6(10), NIST_800-53_AU-6(8), NIST_800-53_SI-3, NIST_800-53_SI-4, FedRAMP, FedRAMP_SI-3, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.4.4, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(a), HIPAA_164.312(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_01.x, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ac, HITRUST_CSF_09.j, HITRUST_CSF_09.k, HITRUST_CSF_09.m, HITRUST_CSF_11.a, HITRUST_CSF_11.b, GDPR, GDPR_32.1, GDPR_32.2, MITRE, MITRE_T1046_network_service_scanning, MITRE_TA0007_discovery, MITRE_TA0010_exfiltration]

- rule: Suspicious OpenSSL Shared Object Loaded
  desc: Detect openssl loading custom libraries
  condition: >
    spawned_process and (proc.name=openssl and proc.cmdline contains "engine" and proc.cmdline contains ".so")
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  - name: image_repo
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [trusted_images, falco_privileged_images, sysdig_commercial_images]
  - name: proc_names
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
  output: >
    Openssl loaded a shared object file. This may be an indication of compromise. (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.name=%proc.name parent_process=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] ggggparent=%proc.aname[5] proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name)
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [process, file, MITRE, MITRE_TA0002_execution, MITRE_TA0003_persistence]

- rule: OpenSSL File Read or Write
  desc: Detect OpenSSL attempting to read or write a file
  condition: >
    spawned_process and proc.name=openssl and (proc.cmdline contains "enc" and (proc.cmdline contains "-in" or proc.cmdline contains "-out"))
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  - name: image_repo
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [trusted_images, falco_privileged_images, sysdig_commercial_images]
  - name: proc_names
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
  - name: proc_cmdline_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.cmdline, container.image.repository]
    comps: [startswith, endswith]
  output: >
    OpenSSL attempted to read or write a file. (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.name=%proc.name parent_process=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] ggggparent=%proc.aname[5] proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name)
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [process, file, MITRE, MITRE_TA0002_execution, MITRE_TA0003_persistence]
  append: false

- macro: socat_localhost
  condition: (proc.name=socat and (proc.cmdline startswith "socat - TCP4:localhost:" or proc.cmdline startswith "socat - TCP4:127.0.0.1:"))

# This rule is not enabled by default, as there are legitimate use
# cases for these tools on hosts. If you want to enable it, modify the
# following macro. Never used
- macro: consider_network_tools_on_host
  condition: (never_true)

- rule: Launch Suspicious Network Tool on Host
  desc: Detect network tools launched on the host
  condition: >
    spawned_process and
    not container and
    (network_tool_procs or openssl_connection or proc_in_malicious_download_tools) and
    not netcat_localhost and
    not socat_localhost and
    not user_known_network_tool_activities
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_pname
    fields: [proc.name, proc.pname]
    comps: [in, in]
    values:
    - [[dig], [diamond]]
    - [[wget], ['"50-motd-news"']]
  - name: proc_name_pname_cmdline
    fields: [proc.name, proc.pname, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, in, endswith]
    values:
    - [["nc"], ["ssh_mfa_metrics"], "/usr/local/bin/ssh_mfa_metrics.sh"]
  - name: proc_pcmdline_startswith
    fields: [proc.pcmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
    values:
    - ["pybin -E /opt/Tanium/TaniumClient/Tools/Discover/"]
  - name: proc_aname_2
    fields: proc.aname[2]
    comps: in
    values: ["consul"]
  output: >
    Network tool launched on host (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.name=%proc.name parent_process=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] ggggparent=%proc.aname[5] proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name)
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [network, process, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.1, SOC2_CC6.7, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.14.1, NIST_800-171_3.14.2, NIST_800-171_3.14.3, NIST_800-171_3.14.4, NIST_800-171_3.14.5, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.14.7, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-6(9), NIST_800-53_AC-6(10), NIST_800-53_AU-6(8), NIST_800-53_SI-3, NIST_800-53_SI-4, FedRAMP, FedRAMP_SI-3, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.4.4, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(a), HIPAA_164.312(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_01.x, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ac, HITRUST_CSF_09.j, HITRUST_CSF_09.k, HITRUST_CSF_09.m, HITRUST_CSF_11.a, HITRUST_CSF_11.b, GDPR, GDPR_32.1, GDPR_32.2, MITRE, MITRE_T1046_network_service_scanning, MITRE_TA0007_discovery, MITRE_TA0010_exfiltration]

- list: grep_binaries
  items: [grep, egrep, fgrep]

- macro: grep_commands
  condition: (proc.name in (grep_binaries))

# a less restrictive search for things that might be passwords/ssh/user etc.
- macro: grep_more
  condition: (never_true)

- macro: private_key_or_password
  condition: >
    (proc.args icontains "BEGIN PRIVATE" or
     proc.args icontains "BEGIN RSA PRIVATE" or
     proc.args icontains "BEGIN DSA PRIVATE" or
     proc.args icontains "BEGIN EC PRIVATE" or
     (grep_more and
      (proc.args icontains " pass " or
       proc.args icontains " ssh " or
       proc.args icontains " user "))
    )

- rule: Search Private Keys or Passwords
  desc: >
    Detect grep private keys or passwords activity.
  condition: >
    (spawned_process and
     ((grep_commands and private_key_or_password) or
      (proc.name = "find" and (proc.args contains "id_rsa" or proc.args contains "id_dsa" or proc.args contains "id_ed25519")))
    )
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_pname
    fields: [proc.name, proc.pname]
  - name: proc_cmdline
    fields: [proc.name, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, startswith]
  - name: proc_aname_4
    fields: proc.aname[4]
    comps: in
    values: [qualys_binaries]
  - name: proc_aname_5
    fields: proc.aname[5]
    comps: in
    values: [qualys_binaries]
  - name: proc_pname_cmdline
    fields: [proc.pname, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [["acme.sh"], "acme-v02.api.letsencrypt.org/directory/account.key"]
  output: >
    Grep private keys or passwords activities found
    (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline container.id=%container.id container_name=%container.name
    evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] ggggparent=%proc.aname[5] gggggparent=%proc.aname[6] ggggggparent=%proc.aname[7]  proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [process, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.3, SOC2_CC6.7, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.13.4, NIST_800-190, NIST_800-190_3.1.4, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_SC-4, NIST_800-53_SI-4(18), ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.4.1, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.w, MITRE, MITRE_T1552_unsecured_credentials, MITRE_TA0006_credential_access, MITRE_TA0007_discovery]

- list: log_directories
  items: [/var/log, /dev/log]

- list: log_files
  items: [syslog, auth.log, secure, kern.log, cron, user.log, dpkg.log, last.log, yum.log, access_log, mysql.log, mysqld.log, vmware-vmsvc-root.log, vmware-root.log]

- macro: access_log_files
  condition: (fd.directory in (log_directories) or fd.filename in (log_files))

# a placeholder for whitelist log files that could be cleared. Recommend the macro as (fd.name startswith "/var/log/app1*")
- macro: allowed_clear_log_files
  condition: (never_true)

- macro: trusted_logging_images
  condition: (container.image.repository endswith "splunk/fluentd-hec" or container.image.repository endswith "fluent/fluentd-kubernetes-daemonset" or container.image.repository endswith "openshift3/ose-logging-fluentd" or container.image.repository endswith "containernetworking/azure-npm" or container.image.repository endswith "registry.redhat.io/openshift4/ose-logging-fluentd")

- rule: Clear Log Activities
  desc: Detect clearing of critical log files
  condition: >
    open_write and
    access_log_files and
    evt.arg.flags contains "O_TRUNC" and
    not trusted_logging_images and
    not allowed_clear_log_files
    and proc_name_exists
    and not fd.name endswith ".lock"
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_file_prefix
    fields: [proc.name, fd.name]
    comps: [in, startswith]
    values:
    - [[vmtoolsd], "/var/log/vmware-vmsvc-root.log"]
    - [["kube-apiserver"], "/var/log/kube-apiserver-audit.log"]
    - [["tomcat-temp-cle"], "/var/log/tomcat-temp-cleanup.log"]
    - [["falcon-sensor-b"], "/var/log/falcon-libbpf.log"]
    - [["promtail"], "/var/log/positions.yaml"]
    - [[containerd], "/var/lib/containerd/io.containerd.snapshotter"]
    - [[containerd], "/var/lib/containerd/tmpmounts/containerd"]
    - [[uspinfo], "/var/log/uspinfo.log"]
    - [["update_promethe"], "/var/log/promtool.lastrun.log"]
  - name: proc_pname_file_prefix
    fields: [proc.pname, fd.name]
    comps: [in, startswith]
    values:
    - [["insights-client"], "/var/tmp/insights-client/insights-archive"]
    - [["gc-launcher", "gc-agent"], "/var/log/gc-enforcement-agent"]
  - name: proc_file_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, fd.name]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [[containerd], "dpkg.log"]
    - [["droplet-agent"], "/var/log/droplet-agent.update.log"]
    - [["fontconfig.post"], "/var/log/fontconfig.log"]
  - name: image_suffix
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith]
    values:
    - ["splunk/fluentd-hec"]
    - ["fluent/fluentd-kubernetes-daemonset"]
    - ["openshift3/ose-logging-fluentd"]
    - ["containernetworking/azure-npm"]
    - ["registry.redhat.io/openshift4/ose-logging-fluentd"]
    - ["grafana/promtail"]
    - ["grafana-loki-acc/promtail"]
    - ["openshift-logging/fluentd-rhel8"]
    - ["sysdig/node-image-analyzer"]
  - name: cmdline_prefix_container_contains
    fields: [proc.cmdline, container.name]
    comps: [startswith, contains]
  - name: cmdline_prefix_cmdline_suffix
    fields: [proc.cmdline, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [startswith, endswith]
  - name: cmdline_prefix
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
    values:
    - ["fluentd"]
    - ["event_loop -r"]
    - ["logrotate"]
    - ["logback-"]
  - name: proc_pcmdline_prefix
    fields: [proc.pcmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
    values:
    - ["fluentd"]
  - name: container_image_repo_in
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [sysdig_commercial_images, falco_privileged_images]
  - name: proc_pname_fd_name
    fields: [proc.pname, fd.name]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [["anchore-manager"], "pytmp/rootfs/var/log/dpkg.log"]
  - name: proc_pcmdline_anames
    fields: [proc.pcmdline, proc.aname]
    comps: [contains, in]
    values:
    - ["fluentd -c /fluentd/etc/fluent.conf -p /fluentd/plugins", [tini]]
  - name: proc_name_aname_fd_prefix
    fields: [proc.name, proc.aname, fd.name]
    comps: [in, in, startswith]
    values:
    - [[executor], [executor, python3], "/var/log/"]
    - [["gc-launcher"], ["gc-agents-wrapp"], "/var/log/gc-k8s-reveal"]
  output: >
    Log files were tampered (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline file=%fd.name container.id=%container.id evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [file, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.7, PCI, PCI_DSS, PCI_DSS_10.5.5, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.3.1, NIST_800-171_3.3.2, NIST_800-171_3.4.5, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AU-6(8), NIST_800-53_CM-5, NIST_800-53_AU-2, NIST_800-53_AU-10, FedRAMP, FedRAMP_AU-10, FedRAMP_AU-2, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.18.1.3, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.p, HITRUST_CSF_01.s, HITRUST_CSF_06.i, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ad, HITRUST_CSF_09.ae, HITRUST_CSF_09.b, HITRUST_CSF_09.x, HITRUST_CSF_09.y, HITRUST_CSF_10.d, HITRUST_CSF_10.j, HITRUST_CSF_10.k, MITRE, MITRE_T1070_indicator_removal_on_host, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion]

- list: data_remove_commands
  items: [shred, mkfs, mke2fs]

- macro: clear_data_procs
  condition: (proc.name in (data_remove_commands))

- macro: user_known_remove_data_activities
  condition: (never_true)

- rule: Remove Bulk Data from Disk
  desc: Detect process running to clear bulk data from disk
  condition: spawned_process and clear_data_procs and not user_known_remove_data_activities
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_pname
    fields: [proc.name, proc.pname]
  - name: proc_name_cmdline_startswith
    fields: [proc.name, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, startswith]
    values:
    - [[mkfs], "mkfs -t"]
    - [[shred], "shred -u /tmp/"]
  output: >
    Bulk data has been removed from disk (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline file=%fd.name container.id=%container.id evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [process, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.7, SOC2_C1.1, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.3.1, NIST_800-171_3.3.2, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AU-6(8), NIST_800-53_AU-2, NIST_800-53_AU-10, FedRAMP, FedRAMP_AU-10, FedRAMP_AU-2, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.18.1.3, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.p, HITRUST_CSF_01.s, HITRUST_CSF_06.i, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ad, HITRUST_CSF_09.ae, HITRUST_CSF_09.x, HITRUST_CSF_09.y, HITRUST_CSF_10.d, GDPR, GDPR_5.1, GDPR_32.1, GDPR_32.2, MITRE, MITRE_T1485_data_destruction, MITRE_TA0040_impact, MITRE_T1565_data_manipulation, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_T1070_indicator_removal_on_host]

# here `ash_history` will match both `bash_history` and `ash_history`
- macro: modify_shell_history
  condition: >
    (modify and (
      evt.arg.name endswith "ash_history" or
      evt.arg.name endswith "zsh_history" or
      evt.arg.name contains "fish_read_history" or
      evt.arg.name endswith "fish_history" or
      evt.arg.oldpath endswith "ash_history" or
      evt.arg.oldpath endswith "zsh_history" or
      evt.arg.oldpath contains "fish_read_history" or
      evt.arg.oldpath endswith "fish_history" or
      evt.arg.path endswith "ash_history" or
      evt.arg.path endswith "zsh_history" or
      evt.arg.path contains "fish_read_history" or
      evt.arg.path endswith "fish_history"))

# here `ash_history` will match both `bash_history` and `ash_history`
- macro: truncate_shell_history
  condition: >
    (open_write and (
      fd.name contains "ash_history" or
      fd.name contains "zsh_history" or
      fd.name contains "fish_read_history" or
      fd.name contains "fish_history") and evt.arg.flags contains "O_TRUNC" and not evt.arg.mode=0600)

- macro: var_lib_docker_filepath
  condition: (evt.arg.name startswith /var/lib/docker or fd.name startswith /var/lib/docker)

- macro: shell_history_env_tampering
  condition: (spawned_process and (proc.env icontains "HISTIGNORE" or proc.env icontains "unset HISTFILE"))

- rule: Delete or rename shell history
  desc: Detect shell history deletion
  condition: >
    (modify_shell_history or truncate_shell_history or shell_history_env_tampering) and
       not var_lib_docker_filepath
       and proc_name_exists
       and fd_name_exists
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_names
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
    values: [docker_binaries, containerd]
  - name: known_shell_history_mods
    fields: [proc.name, fd.name]
    comps: ["=", contains]
  - name: proc_pname_known_shell_history_mods
    fields: [proc.pname, proc.name, fd.name]
    comps: [in, "=", contains]
  output: >
    Shell history had been deleted or renamed (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid evt.type=%evt.type proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline fd.name=%fd.name name=%evt.arg.name path=%evt.arg.path oldpath=%evt.arg.oldpath evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name %container.info proc.env=%proc.env)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [process, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.7, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.4.5, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AU-6(8), NIST_800-53_CM-5, NIST_800-53_SI-7, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.18.1.3, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(b), HIPAA_164.312(c), HIPAA_164.312(e), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_09.b, HITRUST_CSF_10.c, HITRUST_CSF_10.j, HITRUST_CSF_10.k, MITRE, MITRE_T1070_indicator_removal_on_host, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion]

# This rule is deprecated and will/should never be triggered. Keep it here for backport compatibility.
# Rule Delete or rename shell history is the preferred rule to use now.
- rule: Delete Bash History
  desc: Detect bash history deletion
  condition: >
    ((spawned_process and proc.name in (shred, rm, mv) and proc.args contains "bash_history") or
     (open_write and fd.name contains "bash_history" and evt.arg.flags contains "O_TRUNC" and not evt.arg.mode=0600))
     and container.image.repository="sysdig_disabled"
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_pname
    fields: [proc.name, proc.pname]
  - name: known_shell_history_deletes
    fields: [proc.name, fd.name]
    comps: ["=", contains]
  - name: cmdline_prefix_container_contains
    fields: [proc.cmdline, container.name]
    comps: [startswith, contains]
  output: >
    Shell history had been deleted or renamed (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid evt.type=%evt.type proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline fd.name=%fd.name name=%evt.arg.name path=%evt.arg.path oldpath=%evt.arg.oldpath evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name %container.info)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [process, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.7, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.4.5, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AU-6(8), NIST_800-53_CM-5, NIST_800-53_SI-7, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.18.1.3, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(b), HIPAA_164.312(c), HIPAA_164.312(e), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_09.b, HITRUST_CSF_10.c, HITRUST_CSF_10.j, HITRUST_CSF_10.k, MITRE, MITRE_T1070_indicator_removal_on_host, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion]

- macro: consider_all_chmods
  condition: (always_true)

- list: user_known_chmod_applications
  items: [hyperkube, kubelet, dpkg, yum, oneagentos, crtmqm, containerd, systemd]

# This macro should be overridden in user rules as needed. This is useful if a given application
# should not be ignored alltogether with the user_known_chmod_applications list, but only in
# specific conditions.
- macro: user_known_set_setuid_or_setgid_bit_conditions
  condition: (never_true)

- rule: Set Setuid or Setgid bit
  desc: >
    When the setuid or setgid bits are set for an application,
    this means that the application will run with the privileges of the owning user or group respectively.
    Detect setuid or setgid bits set via chmod
  condition: >
    consider_all_chmods and chmod and (evt.arg.mode contains "S_ISUID" or evt.arg.mode contains "S_ISGID")
    and not exe_running_docker_save
    and not user_known_set_setuid_or_setgid_bit_conditions
    and proc_name_exists
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_names
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
    values: [user_known_chmod_applications, systemd, k3s-server, unzip, bsdtar, azurefileplugin]
  - name: trusted_images_sysdig_setuid_or_setgid_bit
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith]
    values:
    - ["sysdig/agent"]
    - ["sysdig/agent-slim"]
    - ["sysdig/node-image-analyzer"]
    - ["sysdig/agent-slim"]
    - ["k8sgerrit/gerrit"]
    - ["qualys/qcs-sensor"]
    - ["docker.io/datadog/agent"]
    - ["k8s.gcr.io/git-sync/git-sync"]
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [[install], "gke.gcr.io/calico/cni"]
    - [[install], "docker/ucp-calico-cni"]
  - name: proc_pcmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.pcmdline]
    comps: [contains]
    values:
    - ["/var/lib/dpkg/info"]
    - ["yarn.js install"]
    - ["splunkboot.sh"]
  - name: cmdline_prefix_container_id
    fields: [proc.cmdline, container.id]
    comps: [startswith, "="]
  - name: proc_cmdline_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.cmdline, container.image.repository]
    comps: [startswith, endswith]
    values:
    - ["microdnf -y install", "openshift-release-dev/ocp-v4.0-art-dev"]
  - name: proc_cmdline_prefix
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
    values:
    - ["tar -C /usr/local/qualys/qpa/data/static_scan_temp/"]
  - name: container_name_image_prefix
    fields: [container.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [contains, startswith]
  - name: evt_arg_filename_image_suffix
    fields: [evt.arg.filename, container.image.repository]
    comps: [startswith, endswith]
    values:
    - [/tmp/minion-permanent-data-storage, quay.io/newrelic/synthetics-minion]
    - [/tmp/shared-volume-, quay.io/newrelic/synthetics-minion]
    - [/tmp/newrelic/synthetics/minion/cache/, quay.io/newrelic/synthetics-minion]
    - [/usr/local/lib/python2.7, buildkite/agent]
    - [/usr/local/share/fonts, buildkite/agent]
    - ["/opt/cni/bin/calico", "gke.gcr.io/calico/cni"]
    - ["/var/run/postgresql", "docker.io/library/postgres"]
    - ["/home/jenkins/workspace/", "/jenkins-agent"]
    - ["/var/jenkins_home/workload/", "/jenkins-agent"]
    - ["/temp-workspace/workspace/", "/jenkins-agent"]
    - ["/var/run/postgresql", "/postgresql"]
    - ["/var/jenkins_home/workload/", "/jenkins_builtin"]
  - name: pcmdline_prefix_proc_name
    fields: [proc.pcmdline, proc.name]
    comps: [startswith, in]
    values:
    - ["pip3", ["python3.7"]]
  - name: evt_arg_filename_proc_name
    fields: [evt.arg.filename, proc.name]
    comps: [glob, in]
    values:
    - ["/var/lib/kubelet/pods/*/volumes/kubernetes.io*", [the-kubelet, kubelet]]
    - ["/tmp/spark-*", [java, "Thread-2"]]
    - ["/var/data/spark-*", [java]]
  - name: proc_anames
    fields: proc.aname
    comps: in
    values: ["s6-svscan", "s6-supervise"]
  - name: proc_exepath_file_prefix
    fields: [proc.exepath, evt.arg.filename]
    comps: [startswith, startswith]
    values:
    - ["/opt/cni/bin/install", "/opt/cni/bin/"]
  - name: proc_name_aname
    fields: [proc.name, proc.aname]
    comps: [in, in]
    values:
    - [[chrome], [chrome, node]]
    - [[executor], [executor, python3]]
  output: >
    Setuid or setgid bit is set via chmod (fd=%evt.arg.fd filename=%evt.arg.filename mode=%evt.arg.mode user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid process=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline container.id=%container.id container_name=%container.name evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag)
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [process, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.6, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.14.7, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-6(9), NIST_800-53_AC-6(10), NIST_800-53_SI-4, NIST_800-53_SI-4(20), NIST_800-53_SI-4(22), NIST_800-53_SI-7, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.2.3, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(a), HIPAA_164.312(c), HIPAA_164.312(e), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_01.x, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ac, HITRUST_CSF_09.m, HITRUST_CSF_10.c, HITRUST_CSF_11.a, HITRUST_CSF_11.b, GDPR, GDPR_32.1, GDPR_32.2, MITRE, MITRE_T1548.001_abuse_elevation_control_mechanism_setuid_and_setgid, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation]

- list: exclude_hidden_directories
  items: [/root/.cassandra]

# To use this rule, you should modify consider_hidden_file_creation.
- macro: consider_hidden_file_creation
  condition: (never_true)

- macro: user_known_create_hidden_file_activities
  condition: (never_true)

- rule: Create Hidden Files or Directories
  desc: Detect hidden files or directories created
  condition: >
    ((modify and evt.arg.newpath contains "/.") or
     (mkdir and evt.arg.path contains "/.") or
     (open_write and evt.arg.flags contains "O_CREAT" and fd.name contains "/." and not fd.name pmatch (exclude_hidden_directories))) and
    consider_hidden_file_creation and
    not user_known_create_hidden_file_activities
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_file_prefix
    fields: [proc.name, fd.name]
    comps: [in, startswith]
    values:
    - [[systemd-network], "/run/systemd/netif"]
    - [[systemd-journal], "/run/systemd/journal"]
    - [[cilium-agent], "/run/cilium"]
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [["agent"], "docker.io/grafana/agent"]
  output: >
    Hidden file or directory created (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline file=%fd.name newpath=%evt.arg.newpath container.id=%container.id container_name=%container.name evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag)
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [file, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.3.1, NIST_800-171_3.3.2, NIST, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AU-2, NIST_800-53_SI-7, FedRAMP, FedRAMP_AU-2, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.12.1.2, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(b), HIPAA_164.312(c), HIPAA_164.312(e), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.p, HITRUST_CSF_01.s, HITRUST_CSF_06.i, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ad, HITRUST_CSF_09.ae, HITRUST_CSF_10.c, MITRE, MITRE_T1036_masquerading, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_T1564.001_hide_artifacts_hidden_files_and_directories]

  condition: (proc.name in (remote_file_copy_binaries))

# Users should overwrite this macro to specify conditions under which a
# Custom condition for use of remote file copy tool in container
- macro: user_known_remote_file_copy_activities
  condition: (never_true)

- macro: remote_file_copy_tools_noisy_cmdlines
  condition: (proc.cmdline="rsync --version")

- rule: Launch Remote File Copy Tools in Container
  desc: Detect remote file copy tools launched in container
  condition: >
    spawned_process
    and container
    and remote_file_copy_procs
    and not user_known_remote_file_copy_activities
    and not remote_file_copy_tools_noisy_cmdlines
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_parent_name
    fields: [proc.name, proc.pname]
    values:
    - ["rsync", "px-oci-mon"]
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  - name: image_suffix_proc_name_fdname_suffix
    fields: [container.image.repository, proc.name, fd.name]
    comps: [endswith, in, endswith]
  - name: proc_cmdline_pcmdline
    fields: [proc.cmdline, proc.pcmdline]
    comps: [startswith, startswith]
  - name: image_suffix_cmdline
    fields: [container.image.repository, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [endswith, contains]
  - name: proc_pname_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.pname, container.image.repository]
    comps: [startswith, endswith]
    values:
    - ["px-oci-mon", "portworx/oci-monitor"]
  - name: image_suffix
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith]
  - name: proc_anames
    fields: proc.aname
    comps: in
    values: ["barman"]
  output: >
    Remote file copy tool launched in container (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.name=%proc.name proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline parent_process=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4]
    container.id=%container.id container_name=%container.name evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag)
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [network, process, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.3, SOC2_CC6.7, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.13.4, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_SC-4, NIST_800-53_SI-4(18), ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.4.4, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.w, MITRE, MITRE_T1021_remote_services, MITRE_TA0008_lateral_movement]

- rule: Create Symlink Over Sensitive Files
  desc: Detect symlink created over sensitive files
  condition: >
    create_symlink and
    (evt.arg.target in (sensitive_file_names) or evt.arg.target in (sensitive_directory_names) or evt.arg.target contains "/var/spool/cron" or evt.arg.target contains "/var/cron" or evt.arg.target contains "/etc/cron" or evt.arg.target contains "/usr/lib/cron") and proc_name_exists
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_file_prefix
    fields: [proc.name, evt.arg.target]
    comps: [in, startswith]
  - name: proc_name
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
    values: ["exe", "containerd", "dockerd", "buildkitd", "executor", "singularity"]
  - name: proc_name_parent_name
    fields: [proc.name, proc.pname]
    comps: [in, "="]
    values:
    - [[bsdtar, tar], '"make-iso"']
    - [[bsdtar, tar], '"make-efi"']
    - [[winedevice.exe], '"winedevice.exe"']
    - [[crio], crio]
  - name: proc_cmdlines_contains
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [contains]
    values:
    - ['"--storage-driver=vfs bud"']
    - ['"--storage-driver=vfs pull"']
    - ['"linkpath=/tmp/iso"']
    - ['"linkpath=/tmp/efi"']
    - ['"linkpath=/tmp/mgticc"']
    - ['"linkpath=/tmp/enav"']
    - ['"sosreport"']
    - ['"gremlin attack-container"']
  - name: linkpath_startswith
    fields: [evt.arg.linkpath]
    comps: [startswith]
  - name: linkpath_prefix_image_suffix
    fields: [evt.arg.linkpath, container.image.repository]
    comps: [startswith, endswith]
    values:
    - ["/usr/local/qualys/qpa/data/static_scan_temp/", "qualys/qcs-sensor"]
    - ["var/spool/cron/crontabs", "qualys/qcs-sensor"]
  output: >
    Symlinks created over sensitive files (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline target=%evt.arg.target linkpath=%evt.arg.linkpath evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [file, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.3, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.14.1, NIST_800-171_3.14.2, NIST_800-171_3.14.3, NIST_800-171_3.14.4, NIST_800-171_3.14.5, NIST_800-171_3.4.5, NIST_800-190, NIST_800-190_3.4.3, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-6(9), NIST_800-53_AC-6(10), NIST_800-53_AU-6(8), NIST_800-53_CM-5, NIST_800-53_SI-3, FedRAMP, FedRAMP_SI-3, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.2.3, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(a), HIPAA_164.312(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.b, HITRUST_CSF_09.j, HITRUST_CSF_09.k, HITRUST_CSF_10.j, HITRUST_CSF_10.k, MITRE, MITRE_T1036_masquerading, MITRE_T1036.005_masquerading_match_legitimate_name_or_location, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_TA0010_exfiltration, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation, MITRE_T1547_boot_or_logon_autostart_execution]

  condition: (evt.type in (link, linkat))

- rule: Create Hardlink Over Sensitive Files
  desc: Detect a hardlink being created over sensitive files

  output: Hardlink created over sensitive files (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline parent_process=%proc.pname oldpath=%evt.arg.oldpath proc.args=%proc.args container.id=%container.id container_name=%container.name evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] ggparent=%proc.aname[4] proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag)
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  - name: image_repo
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [trusted_images, falco_privileged_images, sysdig_commercial_images]

    comps: in
    values: ["adduser"]
  - name: proc_name_oldpath_prefix
    fields: [proc.name, evt.arg.oldpath]
    comps: [in, startswith]
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [file, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.3, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.14.1, NIST_800-171_3.14.2, NIST_800-171_3.14.3, NIST_800-171_3.14.4, NIST_800-171_3.14.5, NIST_800-171_3.4.5, NIST_800-190, NIST_800-190_3.4.3, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-6(9), NIST_800-53_AC-6(10), NIST_800-53_AU-6(8), NIST_800-53_CM-5, NIST_800-53_SI-3, FedRAMP, FedRAMP_SI-3, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.2.3, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(a), HIPAA_164.312(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.b, HITRUST_CSF_09.j, HITRUST_CSF_09.k, HITRUST_CSF_10.j, HITRUST_CSF_10.k, MITRE, MITRE_T1036_masquerading, MITRE_T1036.005_masquerading_match_legitimate_name_or_location, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_TA0010_exfiltration]

# Add rule based on crypto mining IOCs
- macro: minerpool_https
  condition: (fd.sport="443" and fd.sip.name in (https_miner_domains))

- macro: minerpool_http
  condition: (fd.sport="80" and fd.sip.name in (http_miner_domains))

- macro: minerpool_other
  condition: (fd.sport in (miner_ports) and fd.sip in (miners_ip))

- macro: net_miner_pool
  condition: (evt.type in (connect) and evt.dir=< and (fd.net != "127.0.0.0/8" and not fd.snet in (rfc_1918_addresses)) and minerpool_other)

- macro: trusted_images_query_miner_domain_dns
  condition: (container.image.repository in (docker.io/falcosecurity/falco, falcosecurity/falco, public.ecr.aws/falcosecurity/falco, sysdig_commercial_images))

# The rule is disabled by default.
# Note: falco will send DNS request to resolve miner pool domain which may trigger alerts in your environment.
- rule: Detect outbound connections to common miner pool ports
  desc: Miners typically connect to miner pools on common ports(This rule does not work if the outbound connection is made through a proxy!).
  condition: net_miner_pool and not trusted_images_query_miner_domain_dns
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_sport_sipname
    fields: [proc.name, fd.sport, fd.sip.name]
  - name: proc_name_sip
    fields: [proc.name, fd.sip]
  - name: proc_name
    fields: [proc.name]
  - name: proc_name_in
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
    values: ["chrome", "NetworkService"]
  output: Outbound connection to IP/Port flagged as mining activity (dest=%fd.sip proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline port=%fd.sport domain=%fd.sip.name container=%container.info evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: CRITICAL
  tags: [crypto, network, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.8, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.1.1, NIST_800-171_3.1.2, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_CM-7(1), NIST_800-53_AC-17, NIST_800-53_SC-7(3), NIST_800-53_SI-4(4), FedRAMP, FedRAMP_CM-7(1), FedRAMP_SI-4(4), ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.1.2, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.310(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.i, HITRUST_CSF_01.j, HITRUST_CSF_01.l, HITRUST_CSF_01.n, HITRUST_CSF_01.y, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.m, HITRUST_CSF_09.s, MITRE, MITRE_T1496_resource_hijacking, MITRE_TA0002_execution, MITRE_TA0040_impact, MITRE_T1071_application_layer_protocol, MITRE_TA0011_command_and_control]

- rule: Detect crypto miners using the Stratum protocol
  desc: Miners typically specify the mining pool to connect to with a URI that begins with 'stratum+tcp' or 'stratum+ssl'
  condition: spawned_process and (proc.cmdline contains "stratum+" or proc.cmdline contains "stratum2+")
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_pname_parent_cmdline
    fields: [proc.pname, proc.cmdline]
    comps: ["=", contains]
  output: Possible miner running (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline container=%container.info evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: CRITICAL
  tags: [crypto, process, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.8, PCI, PCI_DSS, PCI_DSS_5.1.2, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.1.1, NIST_800-171_3.1.2, NIST_800-171_3.4.6, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_CM-7, NIST_800-53_CM-7(1), NIST_800-53_AC-17, NIST_800-53_SC-7(3), FedRAMP, FedRAMP_CM-7, FedRAMP_CM-7(1), ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.1.2, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.310(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_01.i, HITRUST_CSF_01.j, HITRUST_CSF_01.l, HITRUST_CSF_01.n, HITRUST_CSF_01.y, HITRUST_CSF_09.i, HITRUST_CSF_09.m, HITRUST_CSF_09.s, HITRUST_CSF_10.j, HITRUST_CSF_10.m, MITRE, MITRE_T1496_resource_hijacking, MITRE_TA0002_execution, MITRE_TA0040_impact, MITRE_T1071_application_layer_protocol, MITRE_TA0011_command_and_control]

    comps: [endswith, in, in]
  - name: cmdline_prefix_container_contains
