    - [[docker], ["CM Event Dispat", "instana-sensor-"]]
    - [[oneagentos], [docker]]
  output: "Docker or kubernetes client executed in container (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid %container.info proc.name=%proc.name parent=%proc.pname proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag)"
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [container, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.3.1, NIST_800-171_3.3.2, NIST, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AU-2, NIST_800-53_SI-4, FedRAMP, FedRAMP_AU-2, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.2.3, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.p, HITRUST_CSF_01.s, HITRUST_CSF_06.i, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ad, HITRUST_CSF_09.ae, GDPR, GDPR_32.1, GDPR_32.2, MITRE, MITRE_T1609_container_administration_command, MITRE_T1610_deploy_container, MITRE_TA0002_execution, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation, MITRE_T1611_escape_to_host, MITRE_T1204_user_execution, CIS]


# This rule is enabled by default.
# If you want to disable it, modify the following macro.
- macro: consider_packet_socket_communication
  condition: (always_true)

- list: user_known_packet_socket_binaries
  items: []

- rule: Packet socket created in container
  desc: Detect new packet socket at the device driver (OSI Layer 2) level in a container. Packet socket could be used for ARP Spoofing and privilege escalation(CVE-2020-14386) by attacker.
  condition: evt.type=socket and evt.arg[0]=AF_PACKET and container
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [["datacollector"], "lacework/datacollector"]
    - [["speaker"], "metallb/speaker"]
    - [["nessusd"], "tenableofficial/nessus"]
  - name: proc_names
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
    values: ["oneagentnetwork", "cilium-agent", "keepalived", "speaker", user_known_packet_socket_binaries]
  output: Packet socket was created in a container (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline socket_info=%evt.args container.id=%container.id container_name=%container.name evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag)
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [network, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.8, NIST, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-6(9), NIST_800-53_AC-6(10), ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.1.2, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(a), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, MITRE, MITRE_T1133_external_remote_services, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_TA0006_credential_access, MITRE_TA0009_collection, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escaltion, MITRE_T1557_adversary_in_the_middle]

# Change to (always_true) to enable rule 'Network connection outside local subnet'
- macro: enabled_rule_network_only_subnet
  condition: (never_true)

# Namespaces where the rule is enforce
- list: namespace_scope_network_only_subnet
  items: []

- macro: network_local_subnet
  condition: >
    fd.rnet in (rfc_1918_addresses) or
    fd.ip = "0.0.0.0" or
    fd.net = "127.0.0.0/8"

# # How to test:
# # Change macro enabled_rule_network_only_subnet to condition: always_true
# # Add 'default' to namespace_scope_network_only_subnet
# # Run:
# kubectl run --generator=run-pod/v1 -n default -i --tty busybox --image=busybox --rm -- wget google.com -O /var/google.html
# # Check logs running

- rule: Network Connection outside Local Subnet
  desc: Detect traffic to image outside local subnet.
  condition: >
    enabled_rule_network_only_subnet and
    inbound_outbound and
    container and
    not network_local_subnet
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_proto_sport
    fields: [proc.name, fd.l4proto, fd.sport]
  output: >
    Network connection outside local subnet
    (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline connection=%fd.name user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid container.id=%container.id image=%container.image.repository
     fd.rip.name=%fd.rip.name fd.lip.name=%fd.lip.name fd.cip.name=%fd.cip.name evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name fd.sip.name=%fd.sip.name)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [network, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.1, SOC2_CC6.6, PCI, PCI_DSS, PCI_DSS_6.4.2, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.1.1, NIST_800-171_3.1.2, NIST_800-171_3.1.3, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.14.7, NIST_800-190, NIST_800-190_3.3.3, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-4, NIST_800-53_AC-17, NIST_800-53_SI-4(18), NIST_800-53_SI-4, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.1.2, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.310(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.i, HITRUST_CSF_01.j, HITRUST_CSF_01.n, HITRUST_CSF_01.x, HITRUST_CSF_01.y, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ac, HITRUST_CSF_09.m, HITRUST_CSF_09.s, HITRUST_CSF_11.a, HITRUST_CSF_11.b, GDPR, GDPR_32.1, GDPR_32.2, MITRE, MITRE_TA0001_initial_access, MITRE_T1133_external_remote_services, MITRE_TA0003_persistence]

- macro: allowed_port
  condition: (never_true)

- list: allowed_image
  items: [] # add image to monitor, i.e.: bitnami/nginx

- list: authorized_server_binaries
  items: []  # add binary to allow, i.e.: nginx

- list: authorized_server_port
  items: [] # add port to allow, i.e.: 80

# # How to test:
# kubectl run --image=nginx nginx-app --port=80 --env="DOMAIN=cluster"
# kubectl expose deployment nginx-app --port=80 --name=nginx-http --type=LoadBalancer
# # On minikube:
# minikube service nginx-http
# # On general K8s:
# kubectl get services
# kubectl cluster-info
# # Visit the Nginx service and port, should not fire.
# # Change rule to different port, then different process name, and test again that it fires.

- rule: Outbound or Inbound Traffic not to Authorized Server Process and Port
  desc: Detect traffic that is not to authorized server process and port.
  condition: >
    allowed_port and
    inbound_outbound and
    container and
    container.image.repository in (allowed_image)
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_names
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
    values: [authorized_server_binaries]
  - name: fd_sports
    fields: fd.sport
    comps: in
    values: [authorized_server_port]
  - name: proc_proto_sport
    fields: [proc.name, fd.l4proto, fd.sport]
  - name: proc_names_fd_sports
    fields: [proc.name, fd.sport]
    comps: [in, in]
  - name: proc_names_fd_sports_fd_names
    fields: [proc.name, fd.sport, fd.name]
    comps: [in, in, in]
  output: >
    Network connection outside authorized port and binary
    (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline connection=%fd.name user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid container.id=%container.id evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [network, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.1, SOC2_CC6.6, PCI, PCI_DSS, PCI_DSS_6.4.2, PCI_DSS_2.2.1, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.1.1, NIST_800-171_3.1.2, NIST_800-171_3.1.3, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.14.7, NIST_800-171_3.4.6, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-4, NIST_800-53_AC-17, NIST_800-53_SI-4(18), NIST_800-53_SI-4, NIST_800-53_CM-7, FedRAMP, FedRAMP_CM-7, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.1.2, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.310(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_01.i, HITRUST_CSF_01.j, HITRUST_CSF_01.l, HITRUST_CSF_01.n, HITRUST_CSF_01.x, HITRUST_CSF_01.y, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ac, HITRUST_CSF_09.i, HITRUST_CSF_09.m, HITRUST_CSF_09.s, HITRUST_CSF_10.j, HITRUST_CSF_10.m, HITRUST_CSF_11.a, HITRUST_CSF_11.b, GDPR, GDPR_32.1, GDPR_32.2, MITRE, MITRE_T1046_network_service_scanning, MITRE_T1190_exploit_public_facing_application, MITRE_TA0001_initial_access, MITRE_TA0007_discovery]

- macro: user_known_stand_streams_redirect_activities
  condition: (never_true)

- macro: known_redirect_procs
  condition: (proc.name=ceph or proc.name=google-chrome or proc.name=sshd or proc.name=blkid or container.image.repository endswith sysdig/agent-slim or container.image.repository endswith sysdig/agent)

- macro: image_analyzer_anchore
  condition: (proc.name = anchore-manager)

- rule: Redirect STDOUT/STDIN to Network Connection in Container
  desc: Detect redirecting stdout/stdin to network connection in container (potential reverse shell).
  condition: dup and container and evt.rawres in (0, 1, 2) and fd.type in ("ipv4", "ipv6") and not user_known_stand_streams_redirect_activities
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [[curl], "docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch"]
  - name: cmdline_prefix_container_contains
    fields: [proc.cmdline, container.name]
    comps: [startswith, contains]
  - name: proc_pcmdline_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.pcmdline, container.image.repository]
    comps: [startswith, endswith]
    values:
    - ["timeout 5 bash -c true &>/dev/null </dev/tcp/10", "openstack/extra/rabbitmq"]
    - ["timeout 5 bash -c true &>/dev/null </dev/tcp/10", "general/rabbitmq"]
  - name: proc_pnames
    fields: proc.pname
    comps: in
    values: ["airflow", "beam.smp", "kube-proxy", "containerd-shim"]
  - name: proc_cmdline
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
    values:
    - ["lsb_release -Es"]
    - ["sh /tmp/sysdig-node-analyzer-bin"]
    - ["pgbackrest archive-push"]
    - ["bash /health-probes/health-probe-egress"]
    - ["python3 -c import urllib.parse; encoded_pass"]
    - ["mongodb-mms-aut -mms"]
    - ["healthcheck /scripts/healthcheck"]
  - name: image_list
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [sysdig_commercial_images, "gcr.io/datadoghq/agent", "gke.gcr.io/calico", "quay.io/cilium/cilium", "docker.io/longhornio/longhorn-manager"]
  - name: image_suffix
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith]
    values:
    - ["/hashicorp/vault-k8s"]
    - ["/sysdig/kspm-analyzer"]
  - name: proc_name_pname
    fields: [proc.name, proc.pname]
    comps: [in, in]
    values:
    - [["calico-node", calico], ["calico-node", calico]]
    - [["node-cache"], ["node-cache"]]
    - [["lighttpd"], ["lighttpd"]]
    - [["pilot-agent"], ["pilot-agent"]]
    - [[kubelet], [kubelet]]
    - [["ceph-volume", "ceph-disk-daemo", lvs], [bash, "ceph-volume", "ceph-disk-daemo"]]
    - [[sshd], [sshd]]
    - [[openshift, "openshift-sdn-n", "openshift-sti-b"], [openshift, "openshift-sdn-n", "openshift-sti-b"]]
  - name: exepath_cmdline_anames
    fields: [proc.exepath, proc.cmdline, proc.aname]
    comps: [startswith, startswith, in]
    values:
    - ["/usr/sbin/lighttpd", "bash /opt/www/metrics", ["statsd_exporter"]]
  output: >
    Redirect stdout/stdin to network connection, possible reverse shell detected (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid %container.info process=%proc.name parent=%proc.pname proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline terminal=%proc.tty gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] container.id=%container.id image=%container.image.repository fd.name=%fd.name fd.num=%fd.num fd.type=%fd.type evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name fd.sip=%fd.sip)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [SOC2, SOC2_CC6.6, SOC2_CC6.7, NIST, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-6(9), NIST_800-53_AC-6(10), NIST_800-53_AU-6(8), HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(a), HIPAA_164.312(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, MITRE, MITRE_T1059.004_command_and_scripting_interpreter_unix_shell, MITRE_TA0002_execution, MITRE_T1059_command_and_scripting_interpreter]

- rule: Detect release_agent File Container Escapes
  desc: "This rule detect an attempt to exploit a container escape using release_agent file. By running a container with certains capabilities, a privileged user can modify release_agent file and escape from the container"
  condition: open_write and container and fd.name endswith release_agent and (user.uid=0 or thread.cap_effective contains CAP_DAC_OVERRIDE) and thread.cap_effective contains CAP_SYS_ADMIN
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  - name: image_repo
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [trusted_images, falco_privileged_images, sysdig_commercial_images]
  - name: proc_names
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
  output: "Detect an attempt to exploit a container escape using release_agent file (proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] user=%user.name user_loginuid=%user.loginuid filename=%fd.name %container.info proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.exepath=%proc.exepath image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag cap_effective=%thread.cap_effective)"
  priority: CRITICAL
  tags: [container, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation, MITRE_TA0008_lateral_movement, MITRE_T1611_escape_to_host]

# The two Container Drift rules below will fire when a new executable is created in a container.
# There are two ways to create executables - file is created with execution permissions or permissions change of existing file.
# We will use a new sysdig filter, is_open_exec, to find all files creations with execution permission, and will trace all chmods in a container.
# The use case we are targeting here is an attempt to execute code that was not shipped as part of a container (drift) -
# an activity that might be malicious or non-compliant.
# Two things to pay attention to:
#   1) In most cases, 'docker cp' will not be identified, but the assumption is that if an attacker gained access to the container runtime daemon, they are already privileged
#   2) Drift rules will be noisy in environments in which containers are built (e.g. docker build)
# These two rules are not enabled by default. Use `never_true` in macro condition to enable them.

- macro: user_known_container_drift_activities
  condition: (always_true)

- rule: Container Drift Detected (chmod)
  desc: New executable created in a container due to chmod
  condition: >
    chmod and
    consider_all_chmods and
    container and
    not runc_writing_var_lib_docker and
    not user_known_container_drift_activities and
    evt.rawres>=0 and
    ((evt.arg.mode contains "S_IXUSR") or
    (evt.arg.mode contains "S_IXGRP") or
    (evt.arg.mode contains "S_IXOTH"))
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  - name: cmdline_file
    fields: [proc.cmdline, fd.name]
    comps: [in, in]
    values:
    - [["runc:[1:CHILD] init"], [/exec.fifo]]
  - name: container_image_in
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [sysdig_commercial_images]
  output: Drift detected (chmod), new executable created in a container (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline filename=%evt.arg.filename name=%evt.arg.name mode=%evt.arg.mode evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name evt.type=%evt.type
  priority: ERROR
  tags: [SOC2, SOC2_CC6.8, SOC2_CC7.2, PCI, PCI_DSS, PCI_DSS_11.5.1, NIST, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-6(9), NIST_800-53_AC-6(10), NIST_800-53_AU-6(8), ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.12.1.2, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(a), HIPAA_164.312(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, MITRE, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation, MITRE_T1611_escape_to_host]

# ****************************************************************************
# * "Container Drift Detected (open+create)" requires FALCO_ENGINE_VERSION 6 *
# ****************************************************************************
- rule: Container Drift Detected (open+create)
  desc: New executable created in a container due to open+create
  condition: >
    evt.type in (open,openat,creat) and
    evt.is_open_exec=true and
    container and
    not runc_writing_var_lib_docker and
    not user_known_container_drift_activities and
    evt.rawres>=0
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  - name: cmdline_file
    fields: [proc.cmdline, fd.name]
    comps: [in, in]
    values:
    - [["runc:[1:CHILD] init"], [/exec.fifo]]
  - name: container_image_in
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [sysdig_commercial_images]
  output: Drift detected (open+create), new executable created in a container (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline filename=%evt.arg.filename name=%evt.arg.name mode=%evt.arg.mode evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name evt.type=%evt.type
  priority: ERROR
  tags: [SOC2, SOC2_CC6.8, SOC2_CC7.2, PCI, PCI_DSS, PCI_DSS_11.5.1, NIST, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-6(9), NIST_800-53_AC-6(10), NIST_800-53_AU-6(8), ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.12.1.2, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(a), HIPAA_164.312(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, MITRE, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation, MITRE_T1611_escape_to_host]

- rule: Outbound Connection to C2 Servers
  desc: Detect outbound connection to command & control servers
  condition: outbound and (fd.sip in (c2_server_ip_list) or fd.sip in (ti_c2_ip_list)) and proc_name_exists
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_proto_sport
    fields: [proc.name, fd.l4proto, fd.sport]
  - name: ip_whitelist
    fields: [fd.sip]
  - name: proc_name
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
  output: Outbound connection to C2 server (dest=%fd.sip dport=%fd.sport dproto=%fd.sproto proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline connection=%fd.name user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid container.id=%container.id evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [network, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.6, SOC2_CC7.1, PCI, PCI_DSS, PCI_DSS_1.1.6, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.1.1, NIST_800-171_3.1.2, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.14.7, NIST_800-171_3.4.5, NIST_800-190, NIST_800-190_3.4.2, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_(pending), FedRAMP, FedRAMP_AC-2, FedRAMP_AC-2(4), ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.1.2, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.310(a), HIPAA_164.310(b), HIPAA_164.312(a), HIPAA_164.312(c), HIPAA_164.312(e), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_01.x, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ac, HITRUST_CSF_09.b, HITRUST_CSF_09.m, HITRUST_CSF_10.c, HITRUST_CSF_10.j, HITRUST_CSF_10.k, HITRUST_CSF_11.a, HITRUST_CSF_11.b, GDPR, GDPR_32.1, GDPR_32.2, MITRE, MITRE_TA0010_exfiltration, MITRE_T1041_exfiltration_over_c2_channel]

- list: white_listed_modules
  items: []

- rule: Linux Kernel Module Injection Detected
  desc: Detect kernel module was injected (from container).
  condition: spawned_process and container and proc.name=insmod and not proc.args in (white_listed_modules)
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_cmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [contains]
    values:
    - ["falco/falco_"]
    - ["driver/x86_64/falco_amazonlinux"]
    - ["x86_64/module/scap.ko"]
  - name: proc_cmdline_startswith
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
  - name: proc_pname
    fields: [proc.pname]
    comps: ["="]
    values:
    - ["runmmfs"]
  - name: container_image_in
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [sysdig_commercial_images, falco_privileged_images]
  - name: proc_args_image_repo_suffix
    fields: [proc.args, container.image.repository]
    comps: [contains, endswith]
    values:
    - ["/var/lib/dkms/falco/", "falcosecurity/falco-driver-loader"]
  output: Linux Kernel Module injection using insmod detected (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag module=%proc.args)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [process, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.8, PCI, PCI_DSS, PCI_DSS_7.1, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.1.1, NIST_800-171_3.1.2, NIST_800-190, NIST_800-190_3.4.3, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_(pending), FedRAMP, FedRAMP_CM-7(1), FedRAMP_SI-4(4), ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.2.3, ISO_27001_A.14.2.4, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.310(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.i, HITRUST_CSF_01.j, HITRUST_CSF_01.l, HITRUST_CSF_01.n, HITRUST_CSF_01.y, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.m, HITRUST_CSF_09.s, MITRE, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_T1547.006_boot_or_logon_autostart_execution_kernel_modules_and_extensions]

- list: run_as_root_image_list
  items: []

- macro: user_known_run_as_root_container
  condition: (container.image.repository in (run_as_root_image_list))

# The rule is disabled by default and should be enabled when non-root container policy has been applied.
# Note the rule will not work as expected when usernamespace is applied, e.g. userns-remap is enabled.
- rule: Container Run as Root User
  desc: Detected container running as root user
  condition: spawned_process and container and proc.vpid=1 and user.uid=0 and not user_known_run_as_root_container and image_name_exists
  output: Container launched with root user privilege (proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] user.uid=%user.uid container.id=%container.id container_name=%container.name evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag)
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: ["=", endswith]
    values:
    - ["pause", "k8s.gcr.io/pause"]
    - ["pause", "registry.k8s.io/pause"]
    - ["pause", "amazonaws.com/eks/pause"]
    - ["istio-IP", "amazonaws.com/k8s-addons/istio-proxyv2"]
    - ["docker-entrypoi", "ngnix"]
    - ["cilium-agent", "images/cilium"]
    - ["pilot-agent", "istio/proxyv2"]
    - ["pilot-agent", "istio/pilot"]
    - ["amazon-cloudwat", "cloudwatch-agent/cloudwatch-agent"]
    - ["logspout", "library/logspout"]
  - name: proc_name_image_contains
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: ["=", startswith]
    values:
    - [sidecar, "gke.gcr.io/k8s-dns-sidecar"]
    - ["kube-dns", "gke.gcr.io/k8s-dns-kube-dns"]
    - [argoexec, "quay.io/argoproj/argoexec"]
  - name: image_repo_startswith
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [startswith]
  - name: container_image_repository
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [sysdig_commercial_images, "registry.hub.docker.com/datadog/agent", falco_privileged_images, "docker.io/datadog/agent", "docker.io/amazon/aws-efs-csi-driver", "docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch", "gke.gcr.io/calico/node", "gcr.io/cloudsql-docker/gce-proxy"]
  - name: proc_cmdline_image_repo
    fields: [proc.cmdline, container.image.repository]
    comps: [startswith, in]
    values:
    - ["sh -c curl", "curlimages/curl"]
  - name: container_image_suffix
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith]
    values:
    - ["images/sysdig/kspm-analyzer"]
    - ["stacklight/fluentd"]
    - ["amazon/amazon-ecs-agent"]
    - ["/datadog-agent"]
    - ["datadog/agent"]
    - ["ext-sysdig-node-image-analyzer"]
    - ["/sysdig-vuln-host-scanner"]
  priority: INFO
  tags: [container, process, CIS, MITRE, MITRE_T1611_escape_to_host, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation]

- list: gke_trusted_images_launch_root_list
  items: [gke.gcr.io/gcp-compute-persistent-disk-csi-driver, gke.gcr.io/gcp-filestore-csi-driver, gke.gcr.io/csi-node-driver-registrar, gke.gcr.io/netd-amd64, gke.gcr.io/cilium/operator, gke.gcr.io/cilium/cilium, gke.gcr.io/event-exporter, gke.gcr.io/prometheus-to-sd, gke.gcr.io/fluent-bit, gke.gcr.io/fluent-bit-gke-exporter, gke.gcr.io/gke-metadata-server, gke.gcr.io/gke-metrics-agent, gke.gcr.io/k8s-dns-kube-dns, gke.gcr.io/k8s-dns-dnsmasq-nanny, gke.gcr.io/k8s-dns-sidecar, gke.gcr.io/prometheus-to-sd, gke.gcr.io/cluster-proportional-autoscaler-amd64, gcr.io/k8s-ingress-image-push/ingress-gce-404-server-with-metrics, k8s.gcr.io/metrics-server/metrics-server, gke.gcr.io/addon-resizer, registry.k8s.io/metrics-server/metrics-server]

- rule: Launch Root User Container
  desc: Detect a container being started and configured to run as root. This differs from Container Run as Root User in that it looks for the container started event rather that processes running inside the container.
  condition: container_started and container and proc.exe startswith "container" and (user.name=root or user.name=0 or user.name="" or user.name="0:0") and not user_known_run_as_root_container and not aws_eks_core_images
  output: Container started configured to run as root (user.name=%user.name %container.info evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag)
  exceptions:
  - name: image_suffix
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith]
    values:
    - ["/sysdig/kspm-analyzer"]
    - ["/sysdig/vuln-host-scanner"]
    - ["/sysdig/vuln-runtime-scanner"]
    - ["/sysdig/host-analyzer"]
    - ["/sysdig/node-image-analyzer"]
    - ["/sysdig/compliance-benchmark-runner"]
    - ["/images/cilium"]
    - ["dynatrace/dynatrace-operator"]
    - ["amazon/amazon-ecs-agent"]
    - ["datadog-agent"]
    - ["istio/proxyv2"]
    - ["mcr.microsoft.com/k8s/csi/blob-csi"]
    - ["sysdig-node-image-analyzer"]
    - ["sysdig-host-analyzer"]
    - ["sysdig-kspm-analyzer"]
    - ["/k8s-garbage-collector"]
    - ["/aws-ebs-csi-driver"]
    - ["/datadoghq/agent"]
    - ["datadoghq/cluster-agent"]
    - ["amazon/amazon-ecs-pause"]
    - ["amazonaws.com/aws-for-fluent-bit"]
  - name: image_repo
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [gke_trusted_images_launch_root_list, falco_privileged_images, sysdig_commercial_images, "quay.io/openshift-release-dev/ocp-v4.0-art-dev", "mcr.microsoft.com/azuremonitor/containerinsights/ciprod", "ghcr.io/aquasecurity/trivy", "quay.io/argoproj/argoexec", "docker.io/argoproj/argoexec", "docker.io/grafana/agent-operator"]
  - name: image_repo_image_tag
    fields: [container.image.repository, container.image.tag]
  priority: INFO
  tags: [container, CIS, MITRE, MITRE_T1611_escape_to_host, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation]

# This rule helps detect CVE-2021-3156:
# A privilege escalation to root through heap-based buffer overflow
- rule: Sudo Potential Privilege Escalation
  desc: Privilege escalation vulnerability affecting sudo (<= 1.9.5p2). Executing sudo using sudoedit -s or sudoedit -i command with command-line argument that ends with a single backslash character from an unprivileged user it's possible to elevate the user privileges to root.
  condition: spawned_process and user.uid != 0 and (proc.name=sudoedit or proc.name = sudo) and (proc.args contains -s or proc.args contains -i or proc.args contains --login) and proc.args endswith \\
  output: "Detect Sudo Privilege Escalation Exploit (CVE-2021-3156) (user.name=%user.name parent=%proc.pname proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name %container.info)"
  priority: CRITICAL
  tags: [filesystem, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_T1548.003_abuse_elevation_control_mechanism_sudo_and_sudo_caching]

- rule: Debugfs Launched in Privileged Container
  desc: Detect file system debugger debugfs launched inside a privileged container which might lead to container escape.
  condition: >
    spawned_process and container
    and container.privileged=true
    and proc.name=debugfs
  output: Debugfs launched started in a privileged container (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline connection=%fd.name user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid container.id=%container.id evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [container, CIS, MITRE, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_TA0008_lateral_movement]

- macro: mount_info
  condition: (proc.args="" or proc.args intersects ("-V", "-l", "-h"))

- macro: user_known_mount_in_privileged_containers
  condition: (never_true)

- rule: Mount Launched in Privileged Container
  desc: Detect file system mount happened inside a privileged container which might lead to container escape.
  condition: >
    spawned_process and container
    and container.privileged=true
    and proc.name=mount
    and not mount_info
    and not user_known_mount_in_privileged_containers
  output: Mount was executed inside a privileged container (proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] ggparent=%proc.aname[4] container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline ser.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [container, CIS, MITRE_TA0008_lateral_movement]
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_repo
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: ["=", endswith]
    values:
    - ["mount", "amazonaws.com/docker"]
  - name: container_image_in
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [sysdig_commercial_images]
  - name: trusted_images_sysdig_endswith
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith]
    values:
    - ["sysdig/agent"]
    - ["sysdig/agent-slim"]
    - ["sysdig/agent-kmodule"]
    - ["/sysdig-agent-slim"]
    - ["dynatrace/dynatrace-operator"]
    - ["sysdig/node-image-analyzer"]
    - ["amazon/aws-efs-csi-driver"]
    - ["provider-aws/aws-ebs-csi-driver"]
    - ["ebs-csi-driver/aws-ebs-csi-driver"]
    - ["eks/aws-ebs-csi-driver"]
    - ["gcp-compute-persistent-disk-csi-driver"]
    - ["mcr.microsoft.com/oss/kubernetes-csi/azurefile-csi"]
    - ["rancher/hyperkube"]
    - ["mcr.microsoft.com/oss/kubernetes-csi/azuredisk-csi"]
    - ["mirantis/ucp-hyperkube"]
    - ["mirantis/cephcsi"]
    - ["registry.access.redhat.com/rhgs3/rhgs-server-rhel7"]
  - name: cmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [contains]
    values:
    - ["/kubernetes.io~"]
    - ["cloudera/cm-agent"]
    - ["mount -t ceph"]
  - name: proc_pnames
    fields: proc.pname
    comps: in
    values: ["gce-pd-csi-driv", "aws-ebs-csi-dri"]
  - name: proc_pname_cmdline_prefix
    fields: [proc.pname, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, startswith]
    values:
    - [[dind], "mount -t tmpfs none /tmp"]
    - [[cephcsi], "mirantis/cephcsi"]
    - [["privsep-helper"], "openstack/nova"]
  - name: proc_pname_image_repo_suffix
    fields: [proc.pname, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [["vsphere-csi"], "gcr.io/cloud-provider-vsphere/csi/release/driver"]
    - [["cstor-csi-drive"], "openebs/cstor-csi-driver"]
    - [["aws-ebs-csi-dri"], "gke-multi-cloud-release/aws-ebs-csi-driver"]
    - [["privsep-helper"], "/openstack/nova"]
    - [["aws-efs-csi-dri"], "registry.redhat.io/openshift4/ose-aws-efs-csi-driver-container-rhel8"]
    - [["vmware-vsphere-"], "quay.io/openshift-release-dev/ocp-v4.0-art-dev"]

- macro: consider_userfaultfd_activities
  condition: (always_true)

- list: user_known_userfaultfd_processes
  items: []

- rule: Unprivileged Delegation of Page Faults Handling to a Userspace Process
  desc: Detect a successful unprivileged userfaultfd syscall which might act as an attack primitive to exploit other bugs
  condition: >
    evt.type = userfaultfd and
    user.uid != 0 and
    (evt.rawres >= 0 or evt.res != -1) and
    not proc.name in (user_known_userfaultfd_processes)
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  - name: image_repo
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [trusted_images, falco_privileged_images, sysdig_commercial_images]
  - name: proc_names
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
  output: An userfaultfd syscall was successfully executed by an unprivileged user (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline connection=%fd.name user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] container.id=%container.id evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: CRITICAL
  tags: [syscall, MITRE, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation, MITRE_T1203_exploitation_for_client_execution, MITRE_TA0002_execution]

- list: ingress_remote_file_copy_binaries
  items: [wget]

- macro: ingress_remote_file_copy_procs
  condition: (proc.name in (ingress_remote_file_copy_binaries))

# Users should overwrite this macro to specify conditions under which a
# Custom condition for use of ingress remote file copy tool in container
- macro: user_known_ingress_remote_file_copy_activities
  condition: (never_true)

- macro: curl_download
  condition: proc.name = curl and (proc.cmdline contains " -o " or proc.cmdline contains " --output " or proc.cmdline contains " -O " or proc.cmdline contains " --remote-name ")

- macro: curl_to_localhost
  condition: (proc.name=curl and (proc.cmdline contains "localhost" or proc.cmdline contains "127.0.0.1" or proc.cmdline contains "::1" or proc.cmdline contains "0:0:0:0:0:0:0:1") and not (proc.cmdline contains " -:" or proc.cmdline contains " --next "))

- rule: Launch Ingress Remote File Copy Tools in Container
  desc: Detect ingress remote file copy tools launched in container
  condition: >
    spawned_process and
    container and
    (ingress_remote_file_copy_procs or curl_download) and
    not (curl_to_localhost) and
    not user_known_ingress_remote_file_copy_activities
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_cmdlines
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [contains]
    values:
    - ["vizier-cloud"]
    - ["hub-identity-accounts"]
  - name: proc_pname_cmdlines
    fields: [proc.name, proc.cmdline]
    comps: ["=", startswith]
  - name: proc_cmdline_container_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.cmdline, container.image.repository]
    comps: [startswith, endswith]
    values:
    - ["wget --no-proxy -qO", "docker.io/library/sonarqube"]
  - name: proc_name_cmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.name, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, contains]
    values:
    - [[wget], "http://localhost:8080/healthz"]
  output: >
    Ingress remote file copy tool launched in container (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline connection=%fd.name user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid container.id=%container.id evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [network, process, MITRE, MITRE_T1021_remote_services, MITRE_TA0008_lateral_movement]

- rule: Modify ld.so.preload
  desc: Detect an attempt to write to file /etc/ld.so.preload
  condition: open_write and fd.name=/etc/ld.so.preload
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_cmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: proc_pcmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.pcmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: container_image_contains
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [in]
  - name: container_proc_cmdline
    fields: [container.image.repository, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, contains]
  - name: pname_container_image
    fields: [proc.pname, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [[slkd, "worker-2"], "registry.aquasec.com/enforcer"]
  - name: proc_name
    fields: [proc.name]
    comps: [in]
    values:
    - ["touch"]
  - name: proc_pname_proc_cmdline_startswith
    fields: [proc.pname, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, startswith]
    values:
    - [[crio], "exe / /var/lib/containers/storage/overlay/"]
    - [["dockerd-current"], "exe / /var/lib/docker/overlay2/"]
  output: "File /etc/ld.so.preload has been opened for writing. Possible hidden process attempt (user.name=%user.name proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline parent=%proc.pname proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline file=%fd.name program=%proc.name gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] container.id=%container.id evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)"
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [filesystem, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation, MITRE_T1574.006_hijack_execution_flow_dynamic_linker_hijacking]

# This rule helps detect CVE-2021-4034:
# A privilege escalation to root through memory corruption
- rule: Polkit Local Privilege Escalation Vulnerability (CVE-2021-4034)
  desc: "This rule detects an attempt to exploit a privilege escalation vulnerability in Polkit's pkexec. By running specially crafted code, a local user can leverage this flaw to gain root privileges on a compromised system"
  condition: spawned_process and user.uid != 0 and proc.name=pkexec and proc.args = '' and proc.env icontains 'GCONV_PATH'
  output: "Detect Polkit pkexec Local Privilege Escalation Exploit (CVE-2021-4034) (user=%user.loginname user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name access_args=%evt.args)"
  priority: CRITICAL
  tags: [process, MITRE, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation]

- rule: Base64'd ELF file on Command Line
  desc: This rule detects base64 encoded ELF executables in command line arguments.  Base64 can be used to encode binary data for transfer to ASCII-only command lines.  Attackers can leverage this technique in various exploits to load shellcode and evade detection.
  condition: spawned_process and proc.cmdline icontains base64 and proc.cmdline contains f0VMRgIB
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_cmdlines
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
  output: "Potentially malicious ELF decoded from base64 format: proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline user.name=%user.name %proc.name %proc.pname evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name %fd.name"
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [MITRE, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_T1027_obfuscated_files_and_information]

- rule: Base64-encoded Python Script Execution
  desc: This rule detects base64-encoded Python scripts on command line arguments. Base64 can be used to encode binary data for transfer to ASCII-only command lines.  Attackers can leverage this technique in various exploits to load shellcode and evade detection.
  condition: spawned_process and (((proc.cmdline contains cHl0aG9uIC1j or proc.cmdline contains cHl0aG9uMyAtY or proc.cmdline contains cHl0aG9uMiAtY) and (proc.cmdline contains echo or proc.cmdline icontains base64)) or ((proc.cmdline contains aW1wb3J0IH) and (proc.cmdline contains echo or proc.cmdline icontains base64 or proc.cmdline icontains b64decode)))
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_cmdlines
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
  output: Potentially malicious Python script encoded on command line (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline user.name=%user.name proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname evt.type=%evt.type gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name file=%fd.name)
  priority: Warning
  tags: [MITRE, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_T1027_obfuscated_files_and_information]

- macro: pip_venv_tmp
  condition: ((proc.pname=pip and proc.pcmdline contains "/tmp/venv") or (proc.name=python and proc.cmdline contains "/tmp/venv"))

- rule: Execution from /tmp
  desc: This rule detects file execution from the /tmp directory, a common tactic for threat actors to stash their readable+writable+executable files.
  condition: spawned_process and ((proc.exe startswith "/tmp/" or (proc.cwd startswith "/tmp/" and proc.exe startswith "./" )) or (proc.cwd startswith "/tmp/" and proc.args startswith "./")) and not pip_venv_tmp
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_cmdlines
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
    values:
    - ["chromedriver --version"]
    - ["conftest"]
    - ["sh -c LIVENESS_THRESHOLD_SECONDS"]
    - ["bash -c fail="]
    - ["sh /tmp/apt-key-gpghome"]
    - ["sh -c set -e; TMP=/var/lib/dkms/draios-agent"]
    - ["cat /home/ubuntu/.cache/bazel"]
    - ["touch"]
    - ["python -u -c import io,os"]
    - ["python -u -c import io, os"]
    - ["python -c import io,os"]
    - ["python -c import io, os"]
    - ["python /tmp/tmp"]
    - ["sh ../libtool --silent"]
    - ["sh ../../../libtool --silent"]
    - ["autogen.sh"]
    - ["pip /tmp/venv"]
    - ["docker-bench-security"]
    - ["kubectl apply -f"]
    - ["actions-sync sync"]
    - ["bash ./configure"]
    - ["rustup-init"]
    - ["jq -er"]
    - ["jattach"]
    - ["gitaly-git2go -log-format json -log-level"]
  - name: proc_cmdlines_contains
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [contains]
    values:
    - ["from setuptools import setup"]
    - ["-test.paniconexit0"]
    - ["^helper."]
    - ["^syscall."]
  - name: proc_name_cmdlines
    fields: [proc.name, proc.cmdline]
    comps: ["=", startswith]
  - name: trusted_images_sysdig_endswith
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith]
    values:
    - ["sysdig/compliance-benchmark-runner"]
    - ["buildkite/agent"]
  - name: proc_names
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
    values: ["gcc", "g++", "c1plus", "configure", "cc1", "ld", "collect2", "dummy", "list_repository", "oneagentdynamiz"]
  - name: proc_exepath
    fields: [proc.exepath]
    comps: [startswith]
    values:
    - ["/tmp/go-build"]
  output: "File execution detected from /tmp (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline connection=%fd.name user.name=%user.name proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] user.loginuid=%user.loginuid container.id=%container.id evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)"
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [MITRE, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_T1564.001_hide_artifacts_hidden_files_and_directories, MITRE_T1055_process_injection, MITRE_TA004_privilege_escalation, MITRE_TA0002_execution]

- rule: Base64-encoded Shell Script Execution
  desc: This rule detects base64-encoded Shell scripts as part of a set of command line arguments. Base64 can be used to encode binary data for transfer to ASCII-only command lines.  Attackers can leverage this technique in various exploits to load shellcode and evade detection.
  condition: spawned_process and (proc.cmdline contains IyEvYmluL2Jhc2gK or proc.cmdline contains IyEvYmluL3NoC) and (proc.cmdline contains echo or proc.cmdline icontains base64)
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_cmdlines
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
  - name: proc_pname
    fields: proc.pname
    comps: in
    values: ["ossec-logcollec"]
  output: Potentially malicious Shell script base64-encoded on command line (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline user.name=%user.name %proc.name %proc.pname evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name %fd.name
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [MITRE, MITRE_T1132.001_data_encoding_standard_encoding, MITRE_TA0011_command_and_control, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_T1059.004_command_and_scripting_interpreter_unix_shell, MITRE_T1059_command_and_scripting_interpreter]

- rule: Execution from /dev/shm
  desc: This rule detects file execution from the /dev/shm directory, a common tactic for threat actors to stash their readable+writable+(sometimes)executable files.
  condition: spawned_process and (proc.exe startswith "/dev/shm/" or (proc.cwd startswith "/dev/shm/" and proc.exe startswith "./" ) or (shell_procs and proc.args startswith "-c /dev/shm") or (shell_procs and proc.args startswith "-i /dev/shm") or (shell_procs and proc.args startswith "/dev/shm") or (proc.cwd startswith "/dev/shm/" and proc.args startswith "./" ))
  exceptions:
  - name: parent_proc_bench
    fields: proc.pname
    comps: in
    values: [linux-bench, kube-bench]
  - name: proc_cmdlines
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
  - name: container_image_in
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [sysdig_commercial_images]
  output: "File execution detected from /dev/shm (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline connection=%fd.name user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid container.id=%container.id evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)"
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [MITRE, MITRE_T1055_process_injection, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion]

- macro: stop_security_services
  condition: (proc.name in ("service", "systemctl") and (proc.cmdline contains "stop" or proc.cmdline contains "disable") and (security_services_in_or))

- macro: kill_security_processes
  condition: (pkill_usage or killall_usage) and (security_processes_in_or)

- rule: Tampering with Security Software in Container
  desc: This rule detects common techniques by threat actors to disable runtime security software.
  condition: container and spawned_process and (tamper_cmdlines or kill_security_processes or stop_security_services)
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_cmdlines
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  - name: image_repo
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [trusted_images, falco_privileged_images, sysdig_commercial_images]
  - name: proc_names
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
  output: "Attempt to tamper with security software detected (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline connection=%fd.name user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid container.id=%container.id evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)"
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [MITRE, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_T1562.001_impair_defenses_modify_or_disable_tools]

- list: common_tor_ports
  items: [443, 8443, 9001, 9030, 9040, 9050, 9051]

# NOTE: This is an EXPERIMENTAL rule and only contains a subset of TOR entry nodes. It will be improved upon in the future.
- rule: Detect outbound connections to TOR Entry Nodes
  desc: Clients reach the TOR network through its entry nodes. NOTE This is an EXPERIMENTAL rule and only contains a subset of TOR entry nodes. It will be improved upon in the future.
  condition: outbound and fd.sport in (common_tor_ports) and fd.sip in (tor_entry_nodes) and not fd.sip in (user_known_ips)
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]

  priority: CRITICAL
  tags: [network, MITRE, MITRE_TA0010_execution, MITRE_T1090.003_proxy_multi_hop_proxy, MITRE_TA0011_command_and_control]

- rule: Execution of binary using ld-linux
  desc: A binary was seen being executed by ld-linux. This method can be used to execute programs that do not have the exec bit set and may possibly evade detection measures.
  condition: spawned_process and evt.arg.exe startswith "/lib" and evt.arg.exe contains "ld-linux" and evt.arg.exe contains ".so" and proc.name contains "ld-linux"
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_cmdline
    fields: [proc.name, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, contains]
  - name: proc_pname
    fields: proc.pname
    comps: in
    values: [ldd, runc]
  - name: proc_name_parent_name
    fields: [proc.name, proc.pname]
    comps: [in, in]
  - name: proc_cmdline_startswith
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
    values:
    - ['"ld-linux-x86-64 /bin/run-parts"']
    - ['"ld-linux-x86-64 /sbin/mount.fuse"']
    - ['"ld-linux-x86-64 --verify /bin/btrfs"']
    - ['"ld-linux-x86-64 /sbin/modprobe"']
    - ['"ld-linux-x86-64 /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu"']
    - ['"ld-linux.so.2 --verify"']
    - ['"ld-linux-x86-64 /usr/bin/crio"']
    - ['"ld-linux-x86-64 --verify /usr/bin/crio"']
    - ['"ld-linux-x86-64 --verify"']
    - ['"ld-linux-x86-64 /home/jenkins/.cache/ms-playwright"']
  output: Execution of binary using ld-linux (proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] ggparent=%proc.aname[4] container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname proc.args=%proc.args)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [MITRE, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_T1574.006_hijack_execution_flow_dynamic_linker_hijacking, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation]

- rule: Possible Backdoor using BPF
  desc: A process was seen using BPF on a network socket, this could indicate packet sniffing for use in a backdoor such as BPFDoor. Network diagnostic tools may also trigger this rule.
  condition: "evt.type=setsockopt and evt.dir=< and evt.rawres=0 and evt.arg[3]=SO_ATTACH_FILTER and proc_name_exists"
  exceptions:

    comps: in
    values: ["tcpdump", "oneagentnetwork", "cilium-agent", "keepalived", "speaker", "datacollector", "nessusd", "chrome"]
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  - name: image_repo
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [trusted_images, falco_privileged_images, sysdig_commercial_images]
  output: Possible BPFDoor Attempt Detected (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline port=%fd.sport domain=%fd.sip.name container=%container.info evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [network, MITRE, MITRE_TA0007_discovery, MITRE_TA0006_credential_access, MITRE_T1040_network_sniffing, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion]

- rule: Suspicious Home Directory Creation
  desc: An attempt was made to create a home directory in a non-standard location. This usually occurs when an attacker is trying to create a new, stealthy user to use as a backdoor to a compromised system.
  condition: spawned_process and (proc.name in (adduser, useradd, mkhomedir_helper) and proc.pname in (shell_binaries)) and (proc.args contains /dev/null or proc.args contains /dev/shm or proc.args contains /tmp)
  exceptions:

    comps: [in, endswith]
  - name: image_repo

    comps: [startswith]
  output: Attempted Home Directory Creation (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline port=%fd.sport domain=%fd.sip.name container=%container.info evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [MITRE, MITRE_T1136_create_account, MITRE_TA0003_persistence]

- rule: Reconnaissance attempt to find SUID binaries
  desc: "An attempt was made to enumerate SUID binaries. This typically occurs as part of reconaissance on a compromised machine, where an attacker is looking to escalate privileges."
  condition: >
    spawned_process
    and proc.name=find
    and (proc.args contains "-perm /4000" or proc.args contains "-perm -4000" or (proc.args contains "-perm" and (proc.args contains "-u=s" or proc.args contains "-u+s")) or proc.args contains "-perm /6000")
    and not proc.aname[2] startswith "goss"
    and not run_by_adclient
    and not proc.aname in (security_processes)
    and not (user_not_root)
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  - name: image_repo
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [trusted_images, falco_privileged_images, sysdig_commercial_images, "quay.io/argoproj/argoexec"]
  - name: container_name_startswith
    fields: [container.name]
    comps: [startswith]
    values:
    - ["qcsimagescanning"]
    - ["wait"]
    - ["runner-amd"]
    - ["QCS-Image-Scanning"]
  - name: container_image_repo_endswith
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith]
    values:
    - ["kspm-analyzer"]
  - name: container_repo_startswith
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [startswith]
    values:
    - ["evuedsoacr.azurecr.io/amd-opensil"]
    - ["evuedsoacr.azurecr.io/ava"]
  - name: proc_aname_2
    fields: proc.aname[2]
    comps: in
    values: [qualys_binaries, "ir_agent"]
  - name: proc_aname_5
    fields: proc.aname[5]
    comps: in
    values: [qualys_binaries]
  output: Possible SUID Reconnaissance Attempt Detected (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] ggggparent=%proc.aname[5] gggggparent=%proc.aname[6] ggggggparent=%proc.aname[7] gggggggparent=%proc.aname[8] port=%fd.sport domain=%fd.sip.name container=%container.info evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository evt.args=%evt.args)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [MITRE, MITRE_TA0043_reconnaissance, MITRE_T1083_file_and_directory_discovery, MITRE_TA0007_discovery, CIS]

- macro: java_bash_python_bash
  condition: >
    proc.name in (shell_binaries) and
    proc.pname contains "python" and
    proc.aname[2] in (shell_binaries) and
    (proc.aname[3]=java or proc.aname[3] startswith "http-nio-80")

- macro: java_python_bash
  condition: >
    proc.name in (shell_binaries) and
    proc.pname contains "python" and
    (proc.aname[2]=java or proc.aname[2] startswith "http-nio-80")

- macro: java_bash_bash
  condition: >
    proc.name in (shell_binaries) and
    proc.pname in (shell_binaries) and proc.pcmdline contains ">& /dev/tcp/" and
    (proc.aname[2]=java or proc.aname[2] startswith "http-nio-80")

- macro: java_reads_etc_files
  condition: proc.pname=java and proc.name=cat and proc.cmdline="cat /etc/passwd"

- rule: Suspicious Java Child Processes

    - ["pyspark"]

    comps: [contains]

    - [sysdig_commercial_images]

  priority: WARNING
  tags: [process, MITRE, MITRE_TA0002_execution]
