- list: iptables_similar
  items: [iptables, iptables-legacy, iptables-nft, ip6tables, ip6tables-legacy, ip6tables-nft, arptables, arptables-nft, ebtables, ebtables-nft]

- macro: iptables_options
  condition: proc.name in (iptables_similar) and not proc.pname startswith ufw and (proc.cmdline contains " -F" or proc.cmdline contains " --flush" or proc.cmdline contains " -D " or proc.cmdline contains " --delete " or proc.cmdline contains " -X" or proc.cmdline contains " --delete-chain")

- macro: nftables_options
  condition: proc.name=nft and (proc.cmdline contains " flush " or proc.cmdline contains " delete ")

- macro: ufw_options
  condition: proc.name=ufw and (proc.cmdline contains " disable" or proc.cmdline contains " delete " or proc.cmdline contains " reset")

- macro: ufw_rulesfile_deletion
  condition: evt.type=unlinkat and proc.name=rm and (evt.args contains "/ufw/user.rules" or evt.args contains "/ufw/user6.rules" or evt.args contains "/ufw/before.rules" or evt.args contains "/ufw/before6.rules" or evt.args contains "/ufw/after.rules" or evt.args contains "/ufw/after6.rules")

- macro: firewalld_options
  condition: proc.name=firewall-cmd and (proc.cmdline contains " --delete-zone " or proc.cmdline contains " --remove-rich-rule " or proc.cmdline contains " --remove-rule ")

- macro: firewalld_rulesfile_deletion
  condition: evt.type=unlinkat and proc.name=rm and (evt.args contains "/firewalld/zones")

- macro: firewalls_stop
  condition: proc.name=systemctl and (evt.args contains "stop.iptables" or evt.args contains "stop.nftables" or evt.args contains "stop.ufw" or evt.args contains "stop.firewalld" or evt.args contains "disable.firewalld")

- rule: Suspicious Operations with Firewalls
  desc: Detect deletion of firewall rules, as well as stopping firewall processes. Works with iptables, nftables, ufw, firewalld.
  condition: >
    ((spawned_process and (iptables_options or nftables_options or ufw_options or firewalld_options or firewalls_stop)) or ufw_rulesfile_deletion or firewalld_rulesfile_deletion) and not falco_privileged_containers
  output: >
    Firewall rules were deleted or a firewall was stopped (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] connection=%fd.name user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid container.id=%container.id evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  exceptions:
  - name: parent_process
    fields: proc.pname
    comps: in
    values: [portmap, kubelet, cilium-agent, flanneld, kube-proxy, dockerd]
  - name: image_suffix
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith]
    values:
    - ["quay.io/cilium/cilium"]
    - ["kong/kuma-init"]
  - name: proc_cmdline_startswith_container_image_endswith
    fields: [proc.cmdline, container.image.repository]
    comps: [startswith, endswith]
    values:
    - ["IP -F INPUT CONN /usr/local/bin/istio-IP -p 15001 -z 15006 -u 1337 -m REDIRECT -i * -x -b * -d", "amazonaws.com/k8s-addons/istio-proxyv2"]
  - name: proc_pcmdline_container_image_repo
    fields: [proc.pcmdline, container.image.repository]
    comps: [startswith, endswith]
    values:
    - ["istio-iptables /usr/local/bin/istio-iptables -p 15001 -z 15006 -u 1337 -m REDIRECT -i * -x -b * -d", "amazonaws.com/k8s-addons/istio-proxyv2"]
    - ["istio-iptables /usr/local/bin/istio-iptables", "amazonaws.com/k8s-addons/istio-proxyv2"]
    - ["istio-IP /usr/local/bin/istio-IP", "amazonaws.com/k8s-addons/istio-proxyv2"]
  - name: proc_name_cmdline_prefix
    fields: [proc.name, proc.cmdline]
    comps: ["=", startswith]
  - name: proc_cmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: proc_pcmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.pcmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: container_image
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [in]
  - name: pname_container_image
    fields: [proc.pname, container.image.repository]
  - name: proc_name_container_image
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
  - name: proc_name_proc_anames
    fields: [proc.name, proc.aname]
    comps: [in, in]
    values:
    - [["IP"], ["nomad"]]
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [network, firewall, MITRE, MITRE_T1562.007_impair_defenses_disable_or_modify_cloud_firewall, MITRE_T1562.004_impair_defenses_disable_or_modify_firewall, MITRE_T1518.001_software_discovery_security_software_discovery, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_TA0007_discovery]

- rule: eBPF Program Loaded into Kernel
  desc: "This rule detects the runtime loading of an eBPF program into the kernel. eBPF programs are extremely powerful, and as long as they conform to the constraints imposed by the eBPF verifier (ex: they don't cause a kernel panic), give near-arbitrary control over a target system."
  condition: evt.type=bpf and evt.dir=> and evt.arg.cmd=5 and proc_name_exists
  output: "eBPF Program Detected being loaded into the Kernel. Please investigate. (proc.name=%proc.name proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline connection=%fd.name user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid container.id=%container.id evt.type=%evt.type proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)"
  exceptions:
  - name: container_image_in
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [sysdig_commercial_images, "quay.io/cilium/cilium", "quay.io/kubescape/sneeffer", "registry.luntry.com/luntry/sensor-rs"]
  - name: image_suffix
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith]
    values:
    - ["calico/node"]
    - ["tigera/cnx-node"]
  - name: proc_name
    fields: [proc.name]
    comps: [in]
    values:
    - ["systemd"]
    - ["runc"]
    - ["system-probe"]
    - ["cilium-agent"]
    - ["lxc-start"]
    - ["init"]
    - ["sysdig"]
    - ["snap-confine"]
    - ["TaniumCX"]
    - ["pem"]
    - ["cpla"]
    - ["tetragon"]
    - ["oneagentnettracer"]
    - ["slkcndr"]
    - ["oneagentnettrac"]
    - ["hubble-fgs"]
    - ["nvidia-containe"]
    - ["falco"]
    - ["bpfink"]
    - ["dragent"]
    - ["calico-node"]
    - ["kubearmor"]
    - [security_processes]
  - name: proc_cmdline
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
    values:
    - ["tc filter replace dev"]
    - ["runc:[2:INIT] init"]
    - ["runc:[1:CHILD] init"]
    - ["runc:[0:PARENT] init"]
  - name: proc_aname_2
    fields: proc.aname[2]
    comps: in
    values: ["cilium-agent", "cilium-bugtool", "cilium"]
  - name: proc_name_pname
    fields: [proc.name, proc.pname]
    comps: ["=", "="]
    values:
    - ["tc", "calico-node"]
    - ["bpftool", "calico-node"]
    - ["bpftool", "cilium-agent"]
    - ["bpftool", "cilium"]
    - ["s1-perf", "s1-orchestrator"]
    - ["falcon-sensor-b", "falcond"]
    - ["falcon-sensor", "falcond"]
    - ["event_collector", "ECStateEngine"]
    - ["bpfink-generic", "bpfink-generic"]
    - ["bdsecd", "bdsecd"]
  - name: proc_name_image_repository
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: ["=", endswith]
    values:
    - ["datacollector", "lacework/datacollector"]
    - ["collector", "registry.redhat.io/advanced-cluster-security/rhacs-collector-slim-rhel8"]
    - ["collector", "registry.redhat.io/advanced-cluster-security/rhacs-collector-rhel8"]
    - ["s1-perf", "amazonaws.com/tools/s1agent"]
    - ["kodem-komon-rel", "kodemsecurity/komon"]
    - ["worker", "docker.io/kubeshark/worker"]
    - ["kernel-collecto", "splunk-network-explorer-kernel-collector"]
    - ["elastic-endpoin", "docker.elastic.co/elastic-security/elastic-sec-endpoint"]
  - name: proc_pname
    fields: proc.pname
    comps: in
    values: ["trinity-main", trinity]
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [MITRE, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_T1611_escape_to_host, MITRE_T1547.006_boot_or_logon_autostart_execution_kernel_modules_and_extensions, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation, MITRE_T1068_exploitation_for_privilege_escalation]

- rule: nsenter Container Escape
  desc: This rule detects an attempt to elevate privileges by switching namespace context to a privileged process.
  condition: >
    spawned_process and proc.name = nsenter and evt.args contains '--mount=/proc/1/ns/mnt.' and container_entrypoint
  exceptions: []
  output: nsenter Container Escape (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline container.id=%container.id evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [container, MITRE, MITRE_T1611_escape_to_host, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation]

- macro: curl_socks_proxy
  condition: proc.cmdline contains " --socks" or proc.cmdline contains " -x socks" or proc.cmdline contains " --preproxy socks" or proc.env icontains "all_proxy=socks" or proc.env icontains "https_proxy=socks" or proc.env icontains "http_proxy=socks"

- rule: Detect curl Using Socks Proxy
  desc: "This rule detects curl being run using a socks proxy."
  condition: evt.type = execve and proc.name = curl and curl_socks_proxy
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_cmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: proc_pcmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.pcmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: container_image_contains
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [in]
  - name: container_proc_cmdline
    fields: [container.image.repository, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, contains]
  output: Detected use of curl with a socks proxy (proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname fd.cport=%fd.cport fd.sport=%fd.sport fd.name=%fd.name proc.args=%proc.args)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [process, network, MITRE_T1090_proxy, MITRE_TA0011_command_and_control]

- macro: malicious_cmdlines
  condition: (proc.cmdline="rm -rf /") or (proc.name = "mv" and proc.cmdline endswith "/dev/null") or (proc.name=modprobe and proc.cmdline contains "msr" and proc.cmdline contains "allow_writes=on") or (proc.name=ipfs)

- rule: Detect malicious cmdlines
  desc: "This rule detects the execution of potentially malicious command lines."
  condition: spawned_process and malicious_cmdlines
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_cmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: proc_pcmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.pcmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: container_image_contains
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [in]
  - name: container_proc_cmdline
    fields: [container.image.repository, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, contains]
  output: "Detected use of a potentially malicious cmdline (proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository evt.type=%evt.type evt.args=%evt.args gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname fd.cport=%fd.cport fd.sport=%fd.sport fd.name=%fd.name)"
  priority: CRITICAL
  tags: [process, MITRE, MITRE_TA0002_execution, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation]

## This macro detects executions with commands like "cat lse.sh | sh","bash lse.sh" and "./lse.sh". For "linEnum.sh" and "linpeas.sh" the chance of
## undesired matches on commandline is very low, for "lse.sh" we could see some FPs caused by indesired matches on proc.cmdline field. So we're splitting detection:
## proc.cmdline contains " lse.sh" detects "bash lse.sh" and "cat lse.sh | sh" and proc.cmdline contains "/lse.sh" detects "./lse.sh" execution.
- macro: reconnaissance_scripts
  condition: (proc.cmdline contains "LinEnum.sh" or (proc.cmdline contains " lse.sh" or proc.cmdline contains "/lse.sh") or proc.cmdline contains "linpeas.sh")

- macro: reconnaissance_tools
  condition: (proc.name=amicontained)

- rule: Detect reconnaissance scripts
  desc: "This rule detects the use of reconnaissance scripts."
  condition: spawned_process and (reconnaissance_scripts or reconnaissance_tools)
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_cmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: proc_pcmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.pcmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: container_image_contains
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [in]
  - name: container_proc_cmdline
    fields: [container.image.repository, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, contains]
  output: Detected reconnaissance script executing (proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] container=%container.info evt.type=%evt.type evt.arg.request=%evt.arg.request proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [process, host, container, MITRE, MITRE_TA0043_reconnaissance, MITRE_T1598_gather_victim_identity_information, MITRE_TA0007_discovery]

- macro: PTRACE_exclude_proc_anames
  condition: ((proc.name="5" and proc.aname[3]="log4j-cve-2021-" and proc.aname[4]="log4j-cve-2021-"))

- list: known_ptrace_binaries
  items: []

- macro: known_ptrace_procs
  condition: (proc.name in (known_ptrace_binaries))

- rule: PTRACE attached to process
  desc: "This rule detects an attempt to inject code into a process using PTRACE."
  condition: evt.type=ptrace and evt.dir=> and evt.arg.request in (5, 6, 11, 20) and proc_name_exists and not known_ptrace_procs and not PTRACE_exclude_proc_anames
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_cmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: proc_pcmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.pcmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: container_image_contains
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [in]
  - name: container_proc_cmdline
    fields: [container.image.repository, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, contains]
  - name: proc_name
    fields: [proc.name]
    comps: [in]
    values:
    - ["oneagentos"]
    - ["oneagentdynamiz"]
    - ["helm"]
    - ["createdump"]
    - ["jstack"]
    - ["SwComposite"]
    - ["oneagenthelper"]
    - ["php-fpm"]
    - ["dragent"]
    - ["xagt"]
    - ["chrome_crashpad"]
    - [oneagentdumppro]
    - ["py-spy"]
    - ["rbspy-x86_64-mu"]
    - ["rbspy"]
    - ["strace"]
    - ["s1-agent"]
  - name: proc_name_cmdline
    fields: [proc.name, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, contains]
    values:
    - [["5"], "log4j-hotpatch"]
    - [["5"], "Log4jHotPatch"]
    - [["scanner"], "oneagentdynamiz"]
  - name: proc_name_container_image_endswith
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [[gdb], "amazonaws.com/quay.cnqr.delivery/xpressway/spend-graphql"]
    - [[Dispatch], "agent-docker/cortex-agent"]
  - name: proc_name_exepath_startswith
    fields: [proc.name, proc.exepath]
    comps: [in, startswith]
    values:
    - [["yq", "kubectl"], "/opt/dynatrace/oneagent/agent/lib64/oneagentdynamizer"]
    - [["InjectionThread"], "/opt/traps/bin/dypdng"]
  output: Detected ptrace PTRACE_ATTACH attempt (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] container=%container.info evt.type=%evt.type evt.arg.request=%evt.arg.request proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [process, MITRE, MITRE_T1055.008_process_injection_ptrace_system_calls, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion]

- rule: PTRACE anti-debug attempt
  desc: "Detect usage of the PTRACE system call with the PTRACE_TRACEME argument, indicating a program actively attempting to avoid debuggers attaching to the process. This behavior is typically indicative of malware activity."
  condition: evt.type=ptrace and evt.dir=> and evt.arg.request=1 and proc_name_exists
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_cmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: proc_pcmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.pcmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: container_image_contains
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [in]
  - name: container_proc_cmdline
    fields: [container.image.repository, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, contains]
  - name: proc_name
    fields: [proc.name]
    comps: [in]
    values:
    - ["oneagentos"]
    - ["oneagentdynamiz"]
    - ["strace"]
    - ["oneagentinstall"]
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [[gdb], "amazonaws.com/quay.cnqr.delivery/xpressway/spend-graphql"]
  - name: proc_name_exepath_startswith
    fields: [proc.name, proc.exepath]
    comps: [in, startswith]
    values:
    - [["kubectl"], "/opt/dynatrace/oneagent/agent/lib64/oneagentdynamizer"]
  output: Detected potential PTRACE_TRACEME anti-debug attempt (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline container=%container.info proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] evt.arg.request=%evt.arg.request proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: NOTICE
  tags: [process, MITRE, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_TA0007_discovery, MITRE_T1622_debugger_evasion]

- rule: GPG Key Reconnaissance
  desc: "Detect reconnaissance attempts via find or grep to locate GPG security keys"
  condition: spawned_process and proc.name in (find, grep) and (proc.args contains "secring" or proc.args contains ".gnupg")
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_cmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: proc_pcmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.pcmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: container_image_contains
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [in]
  - name: container_proc_cmdline
    fields: [container.image.repository, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, contains]
  - name: container_image_in
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [trusted_images, falco_privileged_images, sysdig_commercial_images]
  output: Detected GPG Key Reconnaissance attempt (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline container=%container.info evt.type=%evt.type evt.arg.request=%evt.arg.request proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [reconnaissance, recon, MITRE, MITRE_T1552.004_unsecured_credentials_private_keys, MITRE_TA0006_credential_access, MITRE_TA0007_discovery, MITRE_TA0003_reconnaissance]

- macro: detect_lazagne_script
  condition: (proc.name in ("python","python3") and proc.cmdline icontains "lazagne")

- rule: Dump memory for credentials
  desc: Detect attempt to read mem or maps file in process folder to get credentials in plaintext
  condition: >
    evt.type in (openat,open) and (proc.name in (cat, strings, grep, find, xargs) or detect_lazagne_script) and (fd.name glob "/proc/*/mem" or fd.name glob "/proc/*/maps")
  exceptions:
  - name: fd_name
    fields: [fd.name]
    comps: [startswith]
    values:
    - ["/proc/self/"]
  - name: proc_name
    fields: [proc.name]
    comps: ["="]
  - name: proc_and_fdname
    fields: [proc.name, fd.name]
    comps: ["=", startswith]
  - name: proc_cmdline
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: container_image_repository
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith]
    values:
    - ["sysdig-probe-builder"]
    - ["agent-docker/cortex-agent"]
  - name: container_proc_name
    fields: [container.image.repository, proc.name]
    comps: [endswith, in]
  - name: proc_pname_proc_anames
    fields: [proc.pname, proc.aname]
    comps: [in, in]
    values:
    - [["injected_queue."], [cytool]]
  - name: proc_anchestors
    fields: proc.aname
    comps: in
    values: ["BESClient"]
  output: >
    Detected process memory dump to search for credentials (proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname fd.name=%fd.name container=%container.info evt.type=%evt.type evt.arg.request=%evt.arg.request proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [host, container, shell, file, MITRE, MITRE_TA0006_credential_acess, MITRE_T1003.007_os_credential_dumping_proc_filesystem]

- rule: Kill known malicious process
  desc: Detects commands that want to kill known malicious process
  condition: >
    spawned_process
    and (pkill_usage or killall_usage)
    and malicious_proc_names
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_args
    fields: [proc.args]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: proc_name_and_args
    fields: [proc.name, proc.args]
    comps: [contains, contains]
  output: >
    User %user.name killed known malicious process. (proc.name=%proc.name proc.args=%proc.args proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline container=%container.info evt.type=%evt.type evt.arg.request=%evt.arg.request proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [host, container, shell, process, MITRE, MITRE_TA0007_discovery, MITRE_T1083_file_and_directory_discovery]

- rule: Diamorphine Rootkit Activity
  desc: Detect Diamorphine rootkit activity
  condition: (evt.type = kill and evt.arg.sig = SIGSYS and evt.arg.pid >= 0) or (evt.type = kill and evt.arg.sig = 63) or (evt.type = kill and evt.arg.sig = 64)
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  - name: image_repo
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [trusted_images, falco_privileged_images, sysdig_commercial_images]
  - name: proc_names
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
  output: Possible Diamorphine rootkit activity (proc.name=%proc.name proc.args=%proc.args fd.name=%fd.name container=%container.info evt.type=%evt.type evt.arg.request=%evt.arg.request proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [host, rootkit, MITRE_T1547.006_boot_or_logon_autostart_execution_kernel_modules_and_extensions, MITRE_T1014_rootkit, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation]


# This list contains the list of the processes that shouldn't make connections
- list: processes_with_no_connections
  items: [kmsd]

- macro: unusual_network_usage_from_process
  condition: (proc.name in (processes_with_no_connections) or proc.pname in (processes_with_no_connections))

- rule: Unexpected Connection from legitimate Process/Port
  desc: Detect a process that is using a network connection and it shouldn't or is using an unusual port.
  condition: inbound_outbound and unusual_network_usage_from_process
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name
    fields: [proc.name]
    comps: [in]
  - name: proc_pname
    fields: [proc.pname]
    comps: [in]
  - name: image_repo
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [in]
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  output: Detected an unusual usage of connection from process=%proc.name process_parent=%proc.pname, port=(%fd.cport, %fd.rport). (proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname proc.args=%proc.args proc.cmdline=%proc.pcmdline container=%container.info evt.type=%evt.type evt.arg.request=%evt.arg.request proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [host, container, MITRE_TA0011_command_and_control, MITRE_T1571_non_standard_port, MITRE_T1020_automated_exfiltration, MITRE_TA0040_exfiltration, MITRE_T1547_boot_or_logon_autostart_execution, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation]

- macro: detect_lastlog_deletion
  condition: (spawned_process and proc.name=lastlog and (proc.args contains "--clear" or proc.args contains "-C")) or (open_write and fd.name="/var/log/lastlog" and evt.arg.flags contains "O_TRUNC") or (remove and fd.name="/var/log/lastlog")

- rule: Lastlog Files Cleared
  desc: Detect a deletion of logs using techniques and tools seen in real attacks
  condition: (detect_lastlog_deletion) and proc_name_exists
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
    values: [dockerd, useradd, usermod, sshd, boks_sshd]
  - name: proc_pname
    fields: proc.pname
    comps: in
    values: [dockerd, boks_sshd]
  - name: image_repo
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [trusted_images, falco_privileged_images, sysdig_commercial_images]
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  - name: proc_name_pname
    fields: [proc.name, proc.pname]
    comps: [in, in]
    values:
    - [[pgrep], [x11vnc]]
  - name: gparent_proc_name
    fields: proc.aname[2]
    comps: in
    values: ["qualys-scan-uti", BESClient, boks_sshd]
  output: Detected a lastlog records deletion considered as malicious (proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] proc.args=%proc.args proc.cmdline=%proc.pcmdline container=%container.info evt.type=%evt.type evt.arg.request=%evt.arg.request proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  tags: [file, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.7, PCI, PCI_DSS, PCI_DSS_10.5.5, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.3.1, NIST_800-171_3.3.2, NIST_800-171_3.4.5, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AU-6(8), NIST_800-53_CM-5, NIST_800-53_AU-2, NIST_800-53_AU-10, FedRAMP, FedRAMP_AU-10, FedRAMP_AU-2, ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.18.1.3, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.p, HITRUST_CSF_01.s, HITRUST_CSF_06.i, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ad, HITRUST_CSF_09.ae, HITRUST_CSF_09.b, HITRUST_CSF_09.x, HITRUST_CSF_09.y, HITRUST_CSF_10.d, HITRUST_CSF_10.j, HITRUST_CSF_10.k, MITRE, MITRE_T1070_indicator_removal_on_host, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion]
  priority: WARNING

- macro: ssh_redirect
  condition: proc.name=sshd and fd.sport=22

- macro: null_ip
  condition: fd.cip="0.0.0.0" or fd.sip="0.0.0.0"

- rule: Redirect STDOUT/STDIN to Network Connection in Host
  desc: Detect redirecting stdout/stdin to network connection in host (potential reverse shell).
  condition: evt.type=dup and evt.dir=> and not container and fd.num in (0, 1, 2) and fd.type in ("ipv4", "ipv6") and not user_known_stand_streams_redirect_activities and not image_analyzer_anchore and not ssh_redirect and not null_ip
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_pnames
    fields: proc.pname
    comps: in
  - name: proc_cmdline
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
  - name: proc_name_pname
    fields: [proc.name, proc.pname]
    comps: [in, in]
    values:
    - [["mysql"], ["nri-flex", "newrelic-infra"]]
    - [["nri-flex"], ["newrelic-infra"]]
  output: >
    Redirect stdout/stdin to network connection in host (user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid process=%proc.name parent=%proc.pname proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline terminal=%proc.tty container.id=%container.id fd.name=%fd.name fd.num=%fd.num fd.type=%fd.type evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name fd.sip=%fd.sip)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [SOC2, SOC2_CC6.6, SOC2_CC6.7, NIST, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_AC-6(9), NIST_800-53_AC-6(10), NIST_800-53_AU-6(8), HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.312(a), HIPAA_164.312(b), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, MITRE, MITRE_TA0002_execution, MITRE_T1059_command_and_scripting_interpreter, MITRE_T1059.004_command_and_scripting_interpreter_unix_shell]

- rule: Detect cloned process by PRoot
  desc: >
    Detect a cloned process spawned, possible privilege escalation.

  priority: WARNING

- rule: Detect outbound connections to Proxy/VPN

  condition: proc.name in (useradd, usermod, userdel)
  append: false

- rule: Read Environment Variable from /proc files in Container
  desc: An attempt to read process environment variables from /proc files
  condition: container and open_read and (fd.name glob /proc/*/environ and not fd.name startswith "/proc/self/environ")
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name

  - name: proc_name_pname

    comps: [in, in]
  - name: container_image_repo_in
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [sysdig_commercial_images]
  - name: proc_name_container_image_endswith

    - [["slkinst"], "registry.aquasec.com/enforcer"]
  - name: proc_exepath
    fields: [proc.exepath]
    comps: [startswith]
    values:
    - ["/opt/amazon/bin/amzn-guardduty-agent"]
  output: Environment variables were retrieved from /proc files (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline connection=%fd.name %container.info evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [filesystem, host, container, MITRE, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation, MITRE_TA0007_discovery, MITRE_TA0006_credential_access, MITRE_T1552_unsecured_credentials]

- rule: Connection to IPFS Network Detected
  desc: This rule detects connections to known IPFS gateways
  condition: outbound and fd.sip in (ipfs_ips) and not fd.sip in (user_known_ips)
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_cmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [contains]
  - name: proc_name
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
  - name: proc_name_cmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.name, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, contains]
  - name: container_image_repo_endswith
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith]
  - name: whitelist_IP
    fields: fd.sip
    comps: in
  output: A connection to an IPFS gateway has been detected (evt.type=%evt.type evt.args=%evt.args proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname fd.cport=%fd.cport fd.sport=%fd.sport fd.name=%fd.name)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [network, SOC2, SOC2_CC6.6, SOC2_CC7.1, PCI, PCI_DSS, PCI_DSS_1.1.6, NIST, NIST_800-171, NIST_800-171_3.1.1, NIST_800-171_3.1.2, NIST_800-171_3.14.6, NIST_800-171_3.14.7, NIST_800-171_3.4.5, NIST_800-190, NIST_800-190_3.4.2, NIST_800-53, NIST_800-53_(pending), FedRAMP, FedRAMP_AC-2, FedRAMP_AC-2(4), ISO, ISO_27001, ISO_27001_A.9.1.2, HIPAA, HIPAA_164.308(a), HIPAA_164.310(a), HIPAA_164.310(b), HIPAA_164.312(a), HIPAA_164.312(c), HIPAA_164.312(e), HITRUST, HITRUST_CSF, HITRUST_CSF_01.c, HITRUST_CSF_01.x, HITRUST_CSF_09.aa, HITRUST_CSF_09.ab, HITRUST_CSF_09.ac, HITRUST_CSF_09.b, HITRUST_CSF_09.m, HITRUST_CSF_10.c, HITRUST_CSF_10.j, HITRUST_CSF_10.k, HITRUST_CSF_11.a, HITRUST_CSF_11.b, GDPR, GDPR_32.1, GDPR_32.2, MITRE, MITRE_T1190_exploit_public_facing_application, MITRE_TA0001_initial_access]

- macro: touch_timestamp_cmdline
  condition: ((proc.name="touch" and (proc.cmdline contains " -t" or proc.cmdline contains " -d")) or (proc.pname="touch" and (proc.pcmdline contains " -t" or proc.pcmdline contains " -d")))

- rule: Modify Timestamp attribute in File
  desc: This rule detects changes to accessed, modified or created timestamp of files
  condition: open_write and touch_timestamp_cmdline
  exceptions:
  - name: pname_pcmdline
    fields: [proc.pname, proc.cmdline]
    comps: [in, startswith]
  - name: pname_pcmdline
    fields: [proc.pname, proc.pcmdline]
    comps: [in, startswith]
    values:
    - [["centgpo.shar"], "centgpo.shar /var/tmp/centgpo.shar"]
  - name: pname_container_image_startswith
    fields: [proc.pname, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, startswith]
  - name: fd_name_image_suffix
    fields: [fd.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith, endswith]
    values:
    - ["marker-stuck", "/fluentd"]
    - ["marker-liveness", "/fluentd"]
  - name: container_image_repo_in
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [sysdig_commercial_images]
  output: Detected a change on file's timestamps, possible timestomp attack (proc.name=%proc.name file=%fd.name proc.pname=%proc.pname proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.args=%proc.args user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname)
  tags: [host, container, MITRE, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_T1070_indicator_removal_on_host, MITRE_T1070.006_indicator_removal_timestomp]
  priority: WARNING


- list: code_compilers
  items: [clang, gcc]

- rule: Launch Code Compiler Tool in Container
  desc: This rule detects the usage of compilers
  condition: spawned_process and container and (proc.name in (code_compilers) and proc.args contains "-o")
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_proc_args
    fields: [proc.name, proc.args]
    comps: [in, contains]
  - name: proc.name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  - name: container_image_in
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [sysdig_commercial_images, falco_privileged_images]
  - name: proc_pname
    fields: proc.pname
    comps: in
    values: ["cilium-agent"]
  - name: proc_aname_2
    fields: proc.aname[2]
    comps: in
    values: ["cilium-agent"]
  - name: proc_pcmdline_contains
    fields: [proc.pcmdline]
    comps: [contains]
    values:
    - ["/var/lib/dkms/draios-agent"]
    - ["/var/lib/dkms/falco"]
  - name: all_anchestors
    fields: proc.aname
    comps: in
    values: [package_mgmt_binaries]
  output: Detected a code compiler usage evt.type=%evt.type evt.args=%evt.args proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline user.name=%user.name user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.uid=%user.uid user.loginname=%user.loginname fd.cport=%fd.cport fd.sport=%fd.sport fd.name=%fd.name)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [container, MITRE, MITRE_TA0042_resource_development, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_T1027_obfuscated_files_or_information, MITRE_T1608_stage_capabilities]

- macro: excessively_capable_container
  condition: >
    (thread.cap_permitted contains CAP_SYS_ADMIN
    or thread.cap_permitted contains CAP_SYS_MODULE
    or thread.cap_permitted contains CAP_SYS_RAWIO
    or thread.cap_permitted contains CAP_SYS_PTRACE
    or thread.cap_permitted contains CAP_SYS_BOOT
    or thread.cap_permitted contains CAP_SYSLOG
    or thread.cap_permitted contains CAP_DAC_READ_SEARCH
    or thread.cap_permitted contains CAP_NET_ADMIN
    or thread.cap_permitted contains CAP_BPF)

- rule: Launch Excessively Capable Container
  desc: Detect container started with a powerful set of capabilities. Exceptions are made for known trusted images.
  condition: >
    container_started and container
    and excessively_capable_container
    and container.privileged=false
    and not falco_privileged_containers
    and not user_privileged_containers
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
    values:
    - [["cilium-agent"], "/cilium/cilium"]
  - name: image_repo
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [trusted_images, falco_privileged_images, sysdig_commercial_images]
  - name: proc_names
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
  - name: image_suffix
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith]
    values:
    - ["istio/proxyv2"]
    - ["k8s-addons/istio-proxyv2"]
    - ["amazon/amazon-ecs-agent"]
    - ["gcr.io/datadoghq/agent"]
    - ["/twistlock/defender"]
  output: Excessively capable container started (user.name=%user.name user_loginuid=%user.loginuid proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.exepath=%proc.exepath proc.pid=%proc.pid container.info=%container.info thread.cap_permitted=%thread.cap_permitted)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [container, CIS, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation, MITRE_TA0002_execution, MITRE_TA0008_lateral_movement, MITRE_T1610_deploy_container, MITRE_T1098_account_manipulation, MITRE_TA0003_persistence]

- rule: Kernel startup modules changed
  desc: This rule detects new kernel modules added
  condition: (file_creation and (fd.name glob "/lib/modules/*/kernel/lib/*" and fd.name endswith ".ko")) or (open_write and (fd.name="/etc/modules"))
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  - name: image_repo
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [trusted_images, falco_privileged_images, sysdig_commercial_images]
  - name: proc_name_fd_name
    fields: [proc.name, fd.name]
    comps: [in, startswith]
  - name: proc_name_pname
    fields: [proc.name, proc.pname]
    comps: [in, in]
    values:
    - [[exe], [crio]]
  - name: proc_cmdline_startswith
    fields: [proc.cmdline]
    comps: [startswith]
    values:
    - ["exe / /var/lib/docker/"]
    - ["exe /var/lib/docker/overlay2/"]
    - ["exe / /var/lib/containers/storage/overlay/"]
    - ["executor --dockerfile=Dockerfile"]
    - ["exe / /home/rootless/"]
  output: Detected a possible kernel module creation, please investigate (proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname fd.name=%fd.name proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] evt.type=%evt.typeproc.args=%proc.args proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository:%container.image.tag)
  tags: [host, container, MITRE, MITRE_T1547.006_boot_or_logon_autostart_execution_kernel_modules_and_extentions, MITRE_T1611_escape_to_host, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_TA0004_privilege_escalation]
  priority: WARNING

###########################################
# Begin IoC Malware Rules
# Those rules are provided to enhance detection over malwares
# we are recording in the wild.
# Those rules are updated often to keep up with new IoCs we discover.
# Lists/Macros related to these rules are in the threat_intelligence_feed.yaml file
###########################################

- rule: "Malicious IPs or domains detected on command line"
  desc: "Malicious commands detected in pod or host. The rule was triggered by the IP or domains in proc_cmdline"
  condition: >
    spawned_process and proc_args_with_malicious_domain_ip and not user_known_ips_and_domains_cmdline
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name
    fields: proc.name
    comps: in
  - name: container_image_repo
    fields: [container.image.repository]
    comps: [endswith]
  - name: proc_name_container_image_repo
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  - name: proc_cmdline_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.cmdline, container.image.repository]
    comps: [startswith, endswith]
  - name: proc_cmdline_proc_pcmdline
    fields: [proc.cmdline, proc.pcmdline]
    comps: [startswith, startswith]
  output: "Malicious connections to IP or domains detected in pod or host. proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name %evt.args"
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [ioc, MITRE, MITRE_TA0002_execution, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion]

- rule: "Malicious binary detected"
  desc: "Malicious script or binary detected in pod or host. The rule was triggered by the execve syscall"
  condition: >
    spawned_process and (in_malicious_binaries or
    (proc.name in (shell_binaries) and scripts_in_or and not proc.args startswith "-c"))
  exceptions: []
  output: "Malicious binary or script executed in the pod or host. proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name %evt.args"
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [ioc, MITRE, MITRE_TA0002_execution, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion]

# NOTE: This rule is DEPRECATED. The malicious_processes list will no longer be maintained.
- rule: "Malicious process detected"
  desc: "Malicious process detected in pod or host. This rule is deprecated. The malicious_processes list will no longer be maintained."
  condition: >
    evt.type=fork and evt.dir=< and evt.rawres>0 and proc.exe in (malicious_processes)
  exceptions: []
  output: "Malicious processes detected in pod or host. proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name %evt.args"
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [ioc]

- rule: "Malicious filenames written"
  desc: "Malicious files written in pod or host. The rule was triggered by the write operation"
  condition: >
    open_write
    and fd.filename in (malicious_filenames)
    and not fd.filename in (user_known_filenames)
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_name_parent_name
    fields: [proc.name, proc.pname]
  - name: proc_pname_file
    fields: [proc.name, proc.pname, fd.name]
    comps: [in, in, startswith]
  output: "Malicious files written in the pod or host. (proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline file=%fd.filename evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.name=%proc.name proc.pname=%proc.pname proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline gparent=%proc.aname[2] ggparent=%proc.aname[3] gggparent=%proc.aname[4] proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name proc.args=%proc.args %evt.args)"
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [ioc, MITRE, MITRE_TA0002_execution, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion]

- rule: Malicious C2 IPs or domains exploiting log4j
  desc: Malicious connections detected in pod or host. The rule was triggered by IPs or domains that exploit log4j
  condition: >
    evt.type = connect and evt.dir = < and fd.sip in (malicious_log4j_c2)
  exceptions: []
  output: Malicious connections to C2 IPs or domains detected in pod or host exploiting log4j. proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline evt.type=%evt.type evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name %evt.args
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [ioc, MITRE, MITRE_TA0001_initial_access, MITRE_T1190_exploit_public_facing_application]

- rule: Launch malicious container image
  desc: Detect a new container launched using a malicious sha256 image
  condition: (container_started and container.image.digest in (ti_malicious_sha_images))
  exceptions:
  - name: sha_images
    fields: container.image.digest
  output: Container with malicious sha256 image started in your environment (container=%container.info evt.type=%evt.type SHA image=%container.image.digest proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [ioc, MITRE, MITRE_TA0002_execution, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion, MITRE_T1204.003_user_execution_malicious_image]

- rule: Malicious Environment Variable in Spawned Process
  desc: This rule detects a spawned process with a known-malicious environment variable set. An example of this is the Symbiote rootkit.
  condition: (spawned_process and malicious_env_vars)
  exceptions:
  - name: proc_env
    fields: proc.env
  - name: proc_name
    fields: proc.name
  - name: proc_name_image_suffix
    fields: [proc.name, container.image.repository]
    comps: [in, endswith]
  - name: container_image_in
    fields: container.image.repository
    comps: in
    values: [trusted_images, falco_privileged_images, sysdig_commercial_images]
  output: Process spawned with malicious environment variable set (proc.name=%proc.name proc.env=%proc.env proc.cmdline=%proc.cmdline container=%container.info evt.res=%evt.res proc.pid=%proc.pid proc.cwd=%proc.cwd proc.ppid=%proc.ppid proc.pcmdline=%proc.pcmdline proc.sid=%proc.sid proc.exepath=%proc.exepath user.uid=%user.uid user.loginuid=%user.loginuid user.loginname=%user.loginname user.name=%user.name group.gid=%group.gid group.name=%group.name container.id=%container.id container.name=%container.name image=%container.image.repository)
  priority: WARNING
  tags: [ioc, MITRE, MITRE_TA0002_execution, MITRE_TA0003_persistence, MITRE_TA0005_defense_evasion]

- macro: known_root_conditions
  condition: (fd.name startswith /root/orcexec. or fd.name startswith /root/.m2 or fd.name startswith /root/.npm or fd.name startswith /root/.pki or fd.name startswith /root/.ivy2 or fd.name startswith /root/.config/Cypress or fd.name startswith /root/.config/pulse or fd.name startswith /root/.config/configstore or fd.name startswith /root/jenkins/workspace or fd.name startswith /root/.jenkins or fd.name startswith /root/.cache or fd.name startswith /root/.sbt or fd.name startswith /root/.java or fd.name startswith /root/.glide or fd.name startswith /root/.sonar or fd.name startswith /root/.v8flag or fd.name startswith /root/infaagent or fd.name startswith /root/.local/lib/python or fd.name startswith /root/.pm2 or fd.name startswith /root/.gnupg or fd.name startswith /root/.pgpass or fd.name startswith /root/.theano or fd.name startswith /root/.gradle or fd.name startswith /root/.android or fd.name startswith /root/.ansible or fd.name startswith /root/.crashlytics or fd.name startswith /root/.dbus or fd.name startswith /root/.composer or fd.name startswith /root/.gconf or fd.name startswith /root/.nv or fd.name startswith /root/.local/share/jupyter or fd.name startswith /root/oradiag_root or fd.name startswith /root/workspace or fd.name startswith /root/jvm or fd.name startswith /root/.node-gyp)

- macro: gugent_writing_guestagent_log
  condition: (proc.name=gugent and fd.name=GuestAgent.log)

- macro: rpm_procs
  condition: (proc.name in (rpm_binaries, openscap_rpm_binaries) or proc.name in (salt-minion))

- macro: check_process_status
  condition: (proc.cmdline startswith "sh -c kill -0 ")

- macro: login_doing_dns_lookup
  condition: (proc.name=login and fd.l4proto=udp and fd.sport=53)

- macro: add_shell_writing_shells_tmp
  condition: (proc.name=add-shell and fd.name=/etc/shells.tmp)

- macro: somebody_becoming_themself
  condition: ((user.name=nobody and evt.arg.uid=nobody) or (user.name=www-data and evt.arg.uid=www-data) or (user.name=_apt and evt.arg.uid=_apt) or (user.name=postfix and evt.arg.uid=postfix) or (user.name=pki-agent and evt.arg.uid=pki-agent) or (user.name=pki-acme and evt.arg.uid=pki-acme) or (user.name=nfsnobody and evt.arg.uid=nfsnobody) or (user.name=postgres and evt.arg.uid=postgres))

- macro: perl_running_updmap
  condition: (proc.cmdline startswith "perl /usr/bin/updmap")

- macro: coreos_write_ssh_dir
  condition: (proc.name=update-ssh-keys and fd.name startswith /home/core/.ssh)

- macro: azure_scripts_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.pname startswith "bash /var/lib/waagent/" and fd.name startswith /etc/azure)

- macro: sed_temporary_file
  condition: (proc.name=sed and fd.name startswith "/etc/sed")

- macro: python_running_sdchecks
  condition: >
    (proc.name in (python, python2.7, python3.8) and
    (proc.cmdline contains /opt/draios/bin/sdchecks))

- macro: kubelet_running_loopback
  condition: (proc.pname=kubelet and proc.name=loopback)

- macro: rancher_agent
  condition: (proc.name=agent and container.image.repository contains "rancher/agent")

- macro: rancher_network_manager
  condition: (proc.name=rancher-bridge and container.image.repository contains "rancher/network-manager")

- macro: calico_node
  condition: (container.image.repository endswith calico/node and proc.name=calico-node)

- macro: weaveworks_scope
  condition: (container.image.repository endswith weaveworks/scope and proc.name=scope)

- macro: airflow_writing_state
  condition: (proc.name=airflow and fd.name startswith /root/airflow)

- macro: rpm_writing_root_rpmdb
  condition: (proc.name=rpm and fd.directory=/root/.rpmdb)

- macro: chef_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name=chef-client and fd.name startswith /root/.chef)

- macro: galley_writing_state
  condition: (proc.name=galley and fd.name in (known_istio_files))

- list: known_shell_spawn_binaries
  items: []

- macro: nrpe_becoming_nagios
  condition: (proc.name=nrpe and evt.arg.uid=nagios)

- macro: perl_running_centrifydc
  condition: (proc.cmdline startswith "perl /usr/share/centrifydc")

- macro: runuser_reading_pam
  condition: (proc.name=runuser and fd.directory=/etc/pam.d)

- macro: google_accounts_daemon_writing_ssh
  condition: (proc.name=google_accounts and user_ssh_directory)

- macro: fluentd_writing_conf_files
  condition: (proc.name=start-fluentd and fd.name in (/etc/fluent/fluent.conf, /etc/td-agent/td-agent.conf))

- macro: qualys_writing_conf_files
  condition: (proc.name in (qualys_binaries) and fd.name=/etc/qualys/cloud-agent/qagent-log.conf)

- macro: git_writing_nssdb
  condition: (proc.name=git-remote-http and fd.directory=/etc/pki/nssdb)

- macro: plesk_writing_keys
  condition: (proc.name in (plesk_binaries) and fd.name startswith /etc/sw/keys)

- macro: plesk_install_writing_apache_conf
  condition: (proc.cmdline startswith "bash -hB /usr/lib/plesk-9.0/services/webserver.apache configure" and fd.name="/etc/apache2/apache2.conf.tmp")

- macro: xmlcatalog_writing_files
  condition: (proc.name=update-xmlcatal and fd.directory=/etc/xml)

- macro: supervise_writing_status
  condition: (proc.name in (supervise,svc) and fd.name startswith "/etc/sb/")

- macro: pki_realm_writing_realms
  condition: (proc.cmdline startswith "bash /usr/local/lib/pki/pki-realm" and fd.name startswith /etc/pki/realms)

- macro: htpasswd_writing_passwd
  condition: (proc.name=htpasswd and fd.name=/etc/nginx/.htpasswd)

- macro: ovsdb_writing_openvswitch
  condition: (proc.name=ovsdb-server and fd.directory=/etc/openvswitch)

- macro: datadog_writing_conf
  condition: ((proc.cmdline startswith "python /opt/datadog-agent" or proc.cmdline startswith "entrypoint.sh /entrypoint.sh datadog start" or proc.cmdline startswith "agent.py /opt/datadog-agent") and fd.name startswith "/etc/dd-agent")

- macro: curl_writing_pki_db
  condition: (proc.name=curl and fd.directory=/etc/pki/nssdb)

- macro: haproxy_writing_conf
  condition: ((proc.name in (update-haproxy-,haproxy_reload.) or proc.pname in (update-haproxy-,haproxy_reload,haproxy_reload.)) and (fd.name=/etc/openvpn/client.map or fd.name startswith /etc/haproxy))

- macro: java_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name=java and fd.name=/etc/.java/.systemPrefs/.system.lock)

- macro: rabbitmq_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name=rabbitmq-server and fd.directory=/etc/rabbitmq)

- macro: rook_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name=toolbox.sh and container.image.repository=rook/toolbox and fd.directory=/etc/ceph)

- macro: php_handlers_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name=php_handlers_co and fd.name=/etc/psa/php_versions.json)

- macro: cron_start_writing_pam_env
  condition: (proc.cmdline="bash /usr/sbin/start-cron" and fd.name=/etc/security/pam_env.conf)

- macro: httpd_writing_conf_logs
  condition: (proc.name=httpd and fd.name startswith /etc/httpd/)

- macro: mysql_writing_conf
  condition: >
    ((proc.name in (start-mysql.sh, run-mysqld) or proc.pname=start-mysql.sh) and
     (fd.name startswith /etc/mysql or fd.directory=/etc/my.cnf.d))

- macro: openvpn_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name in (openvpn,openvpn-entrypo) and fd.name startswith /etc/openvpn)

- macro: countly_writing_nginx_conf
  condition: (proc.cmdline startswith "nodejs /opt/countly/bin" and fd.name startswith /etc/nginx)

- macro: ms_scx_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name in (GetLinuxOS.sh) and fd.name startswith /etc/opt/microsoft/scx)

- macro: azure_networkwatcher_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name in (NetworkWatcherA) and fd.name=/etc/init.d/AzureNetworkWatcherAgent)

- macro: update_texmf_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name=update-texmf and fd.name startswith /etc/texmf)

- macro: slapadd_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name=slapadd and fd.name startswith /etc/ldap)

- macro: symantec_writing_conf
  condition: >
    ((proc.name=symcfgd and fd.name startswith /etc/symantec) or
     (proc.name=navdefutil and fd.name=/etc/symc-defutils.conf))

- macro: liveupdate_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.cmdline startswith "java LiveUpdate" and fd.name in (/etc/liveupdate.conf, /etc/Product.Catalog.JavaLiveUpdate))

- macro: selinux_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name in (semodule,genhomedircon,sefcontext_comp) and fd.name startswith /etc/selinux)

- macro: nginx_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name in (nginx,nginx-ingress-c,nginx-ingress) and (fd.name startswith /etc/nginx or fd.name startswith /etc/ingress-controller))

- macro: chef_client_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.pcmdline startswith "chef-client /opt/gitlab" and fd.name startswith /etc/gitlab)

- macro: centrify_writing_krb
  condition: (proc.name in (adjoin,addns) and fd.name startswith /etc/krb5)

- macro: ipsec_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name=start-ipsec.sh and fd.directory=/etc/ipsec)

- macro: userhelper_writing_etc_security
  condition: (proc.name=userhelper and fd.name startswith /etc/security)

- macro: pkgmgmt_progs_writing_pki
  condition: >
    (proc.name=urlgrabber-ext- and proc.pname in (yum, yum-cron, repoquery) and
     (fd.name startswith /etc/pkt/nssdb or fd.name startswith /etc/pki/nssdb))

- macro: update_ca_trust_writing_pki
  condition: (proc.pname=update-ca-trust and proc.name=trust and fd.name startswith /etc/pki)

- macro: brandbot_writing_os_release
  condition: proc.name=brandbot and fd.name="/etc/os-release"

- macro: redis_writing_conf
  condition: >
    (proc.name in (run-redis, redis-launcher.) and (fd.name="/etc/redis.conf" or fd.name startswith "/etc/redis"))

- macro: openldap_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.pname=run-openldap.sh and fd.name startswith /etc/openldap)

- macro: ucpagent_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name=apiserver and container.image.repository=docker/ucp-agent and fd.name=/etc/authorization_config.cfg)

- macro: iscsi_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name=iscsiadm and fd.name startswith /etc/iscsi)

- macro: istio_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name=pilot-agent and fd.name startswith /etc/istio)

- macro: ufw_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name=ufw and fd.directory=/etc/ufw)

- macro: calico_writing_conf
  condition: >
    (((proc.name = calico-node) or
      (container.image.repository=gcr.io/projectcalico-org/node and proc.name in (start_runit, cp)) or
      (container.image.repository=gcr.io/projectcalico-org/cni and proc.name=sed))
     and fd.name startswith /etc/calico)

- macro: prometheus_conf_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name=prometheus-conf and fd.name startswith /etc/prometheus/config_out)

- macro: openshift_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name=oc and fd.name startswith /etc/origin/node)

- macro: keepalived_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name=keepalived and fd.name=/etc/keepalived/keepalived.conf)

- macro: checkpoint_writing_state
  condition: (proc.name=checkpoint and container.image.repository contains "coreos/pod-checkpointer" and fd.name startswith "/etc/kubernetes")

- macro: cloud_init_writing_ssh
  condition: (proc.name=cloud-init and user_ssh_directory)

- macro: consul_running_net_scripts
  condition: (proc.pname=consul and (proc.cmdline startswith "sh -c curl" or proc.cmdline startswith "sh -c nc"))

- macro: consul_running_alert_checks
  condition: (proc.pname=consul and proc.cmdline startswith "sh -c /bin/consul-alerts")

- macro: nginx_starting_nginx
  condition: (proc.pname=nginx and proc.cmdline contains "/usr/sbin/nginx -c /etc/nginx/nginx.conf")

- macro: nginx_running_aws_s3_cp
  condition: (proc.pname=nginx and proc.cmdline startswith "sh -c /usr/local/bin/aws s3 cp")

- macro: serf_script
  condition: (proc.cmdline startswith "sh -c serf")

- macro: splunk_running_forwarder
  condition: (proc.pname=splunkd and proc.cmdline startswith "sh -c /opt/splunkforwarder")

- macro: postgres_running_wal_e
  condition: (proc.pname=postgres and proc.cmdline startswith "sh -c envdir /etc/wal-e.d/env /usr/local/bin/wal-e")

- macro: rabbitmq_running_scripts
  condition: >
    (proc.pname=beam.smp and
    (proc.cmdline startswith "sh -c exec ps" or
     proc.cmdline startswith "sh -c exec inet_gethost" or
     proc.cmdline= "sh -s unix:cmd" or
     proc.cmdline= "sh -c exec /bin/sh -s unix:cmd 2>&1"))

- macro: automount_using_mtab
  condition: (proc.pname = automount and fd.name startswith /etc/mtab)

- macro: mcafee_writing_cma_d
  condition: (proc.name=macompatsvc and fd.directory=/etc/cma.d)

- macro: avinetworks_supervisor_writing_ssh
  condition: >
    (proc.cmdline="se_supervisor.p /opt/avi/scripts/se_supervisor.py -d" and
      (fd.name startswith /etc/ssh/known_host_ or
       fd.name startswith /etc/ssh/ssh_monitor_config_ or
       fd.name startswith /etc/ssh/ssh_config_))

- macro: multipath_writing_conf
  condition: (proc.name = multipath and fd.name startswith /etc/multipath/)

- macro: mysqlsh_writing_state
  condition: (proc.name=mysqlsh and fd.directory=/root/.mysqlsh)


###########################################
# End compatibility-only macros
###########################################

# Application rules have moved to application_rules.yaml. Please look
# there if you want to enable them by adding to
# falco_rules.local.yaml.
